WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:23.625 --> 00:00:26.250
<i>Let's go. let's go back</i>

3
00:00:26.333 --> 00:00:27.416
EAT PRAY BARK

4
00:00:28.458 --> 00:00:33.250
<i>Darling. when you let go</i>
<i>Can't go back</i>

5
00:00:33.333 --> 00:00:35.125
<i>Life is more fulfilling…</i>

6
00:00:35.208 --> 00:00:36.625
- Not now!
<i>- …with a dog.</i>

7
00:00:38.041 --> 00:00:40.791
{\an8}<i>Dog owners are happier people.</i>

8
00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:44.833
{\an8}DOG TRAINING FOR BEGINNERS

9
00:00:44.916 --> 00:00:48.833
{\an8}<i>They remind us to appreciate</i>
<i>the little things in life</i>…

10
00:00:49.958 --> 00:00:52.291
{\an8}<i>…and to always live in the moment.</i>

11
00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:02.250
{\an8}<i>Dogs are naturally curious.</i>

12
00:01:05.625 --> 00:01:08.458
{\an8}<i>They love to explore your world with you.</i>

13
00:01:08.541 --> 00:01:10.416
{\an8}You little shit. I'm gonna kill you.

14
00:01:14.750 --> 00:01:16.250
{\an8}<i>Living with a dog…</i>

15
00:01:16.333 --> 00:01:18.083
{\an8}Drop it! Drop it right now!

16
00:01:19.666 --> 00:01:22.375
{\an8}<i>…increases your life expectancy.</i>

17
00:01:24.708 --> 00:01:26.916
{\an8}<i>Daily walks</i>
<i>with your dog is a perfect way…</i>

18
00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:28.291
{\an8}Not so fast. Torsten.

19
00:01:28.375 --> 00:01:30.625
{\an8}<i>…to get exercise. and to relax.</i>

20
00:01:32.041 --> 00:01:34.041
{\an8}Torsten. come! Heel! Torsten. this way!

21
00:01:34.125 --> 00:01:37.166
{\an8}<i>A dog makes it easy to make friends.</i>

22
00:01:37.250 --> 00:01:39.291
{\an8}Ugh… Whoa. what the hell?

23
00:01:39.375 --> 00:01:41.541
{\an8}- Uh. hey. what is it?
- Hello!

24
00:01:41.625 --> 00:01:45.291
{\an8}Hi. hi… This is Torsten. He's a sweet boy.

25
00:01:45.375 --> 00:01:48.750
{\an8}- No dogs in my car. Out.
- I said I was bringing a dog on the app.

26
00:01:48.833 --> 00:01:51.291
{\an8}I said no dogs in my car.

27
00:01:51.375 --> 00:01:53.166
{\an8}I guess I clicked the wrong thing.

28
00:01:53.250 --> 00:01:55.166
{\an8}Is that coriander? It's so calming!

29
00:01:55.250 --> 00:01:56.208
{\an8}CANCEL RIDE

30
00:01:56.291 --> 00:01:57.458
{\an8}Out!

31
00:01:58.208 --> 00:01:59.583
{\an8}Oh my.

32
00:01:59.666 --> 00:02:01.500
{\an8}Okay. come on. Torsten. It's time to go.

33
00:02:01.583 --> 00:02:05.666
{\an8}Torsten. come! Torsten. we wanted to show
how well behaved you are!

34
00:02:07.791 --> 00:02:09.041
{\an8}Torsten.

35
00:02:09.666 --> 00:02:11.416
{\an8}No worries. it's all good.

36
00:02:13.375 --> 00:02:17.083
{\an8}Oh… 'kay. Thanks. anyway.

37
00:02:18.125 --> 00:02:21.875
{\an8}<i>A dog brings people</i>
<i>who love each other even closer.</i>

38
00:02:21.958 --> 00:02:25.666
{\an8}<i>Shared experiences become</i>
<i>unforgettable memories.</i>

39
00:02:26.291 --> 00:02:27.208
{\an8}For you.

40
00:02:27.291 --> 00:02:29.125
{\an8}Oh crap!

41
00:02:29.208 --> 00:02:30.916
{\an8}Oh my God!

42
00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:32.791
{\an8}- Well. it's not my fault.
- So it's my fault?

43
00:02:32.875 --> 00:02:34.791
{\an8}- The dog's fault.
- The dog has a name. Helmut!

44
00:02:34.875 --> 00:02:36.083
{\an8}Your dog bites me!

45
00:02:36.166 --> 00:02:37.875
{\an8}Every time.

46
00:02:38.541 --> 00:02:40.708
{\an8}Hey. back! Let me finish packing. okay?

47
00:02:44.458 --> 00:02:48.083
{\an8}<i>The most precious gift</i>
<i>a dog gives you is their complete trust.</i>

48
00:02:49.375 --> 00:02:51.875
{\an8}She's officially your dog now. Congrats!

49
00:02:51.958 --> 00:02:55.041
{\an8}<i>- …the foundation of any relationship…</i>
- It's great you're listening to the book.

50
00:02:55.125 --> 00:02:57.375
{\an8}Less great that
you're not completely packed yet.

51
00:02:57.458 --> 00:02:59.000
{\an8}Do you want to miss your train?

52
00:02:59.083 --> 00:03:00.250
{\an8}<i>With a dog by your side…</i>

53
00:03:00.333 --> 00:03:03.166
{\an8}They're airing that report
about you on <i>Morning Magazine.</i>

54
00:03:03.708 --> 00:03:06.041
{\an8}- I'll take you to the station myself.
- Ah!

55
00:03:06.125 --> 00:03:08.333
{\an8}If you really want to help.
keep that dog away from me.

56
00:03:09.333 --> 00:03:10.625
{\an8}Be sweet to that pooch.

57
00:03:10.708 --> 00:03:12.708
{\an8}It's your chance to move on
from this messy business.

58
00:03:12.791 --> 00:03:15.083
{\an8}I have a law degree. A doctorate.

59
00:03:15.166 --> 00:03:18.125
{\an8}I have worked at the Brookings Institute
for years. But now you tell me

60
00:03:18.208 --> 00:03:21.625
{\an8}that adopting a dog will be
the only chance to save my entire career?

61
00:03:21.708 --> 00:03:23.125
{\an8}You know it's true.

62
00:03:23.208 --> 00:03:24.750
{\an8}This dog is totally deranged.

63
00:03:24.833 --> 00:03:26.750
{\an8}Didn't the shelter have any normal pets?

64
00:03:26.833 --> 00:03:29.958
{\an8}Yeah. it's been tough for you and Gaga.

65
00:03:30.041 --> 00:03:31.416
{\an8}But now we'll get help!

66
00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:33.541
{\an8}This guy Nodon is a genius. so they say.

67
00:03:33.625 --> 00:03:36.166
Ziggy. you've raved
about every dog trainer we've had.

68
00:03:36.833 --> 00:03:39.541
But instead of help.
we wind up with a bill.

69
00:03:39.625 --> 00:03:41.416
Yeah… not this time. Okay?

70
00:03:41.500 --> 00:03:44.166
I hope you're right. because
if we can't fix this. I'm moving out.

71
00:03:44.791 --> 00:03:45.625
Ugh!

72
00:03:45.708 --> 00:03:47.000
It's vending machine coffee.

73
00:03:47.083 --> 00:03:50.375
Yeah. Does the precious professor need
a fancy blend to get through the day?

74
00:03:50.458 --> 00:03:53.291
It's not about one being fancy.
I don't want to drink shitty coffee.

75
00:03:53.375 --> 00:03:54.458
Snob.

76
00:03:54.541 --> 00:03:56.125
Hey. hey!

77
00:03:56.208 --> 00:03:58.333
- Whoa…
- Shh. shh! Stop it… Hey.

78
00:03:58.416 --> 00:03:59.875
Shh! That's enough.

79
00:03:59.958 --> 00:04:01.666
Stop it… Now. come.

80
00:04:02.333 --> 00:04:03.791
Roxy.

81
00:04:03.875 --> 00:04:07.125
Shut up. or I'll cut your throat.

82
00:04:07.208 --> 00:04:08.708
<i>Ursula Brandmeier.</i>

83
00:04:08.791 --> 00:04:11.458
<i>Bavarian State Minister for</i>
<i>the Environment and Consumer Protection.</i>

84
00:04:11.541 --> 00:04:14.833
<i>and her party's top candidate</i>
<i>in the coming election.</i>

85
00:04:14.916 --> 00:04:16.708
<i>That was a great discussion</i>
<i>regarding views</i>

86
00:04:16.791 --> 00:04:19.750
<i>on whether pet ownership</i>
<i>is a burden on the climate.</i>

87
00:04:20.458 --> 00:04:22.791
<i>I think a majority of pet owners</i>
<i>can now breathe easier.</i>

88
00:04:23.416 --> 00:04:25.916
<i>And we've cut to a clip. Thanks. everyone.</i>

89
00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:28.208
<i>- Do you actually own a dog?</i>
<i>- Oh God. no.</i>

90
00:04:28.291 --> 00:04:31.416
<i>I'd much rather poke out my eyes than</i>
<i>have one of those brutes in my house.</i>

91
00:04:31.500 --> 00:04:33.791
<i>For many. their dog is their most</i>

92
00:04:33.875 --> 00:04:35.333
significant life partner.

93
00:04:35.416 --> 00:04:40.541
Wow. if my pet was my significant
life partner. you might as well kill me.

94
00:04:41.125 --> 00:04:42.750
<i>We had a problem with the clip.</i>

95
00:04:42.833 --> 00:04:46.500
I was just told that
there was an issue with the clip.

96
00:04:46.583 --> 00:04:47.875
We were still on air.

97
00:04:51.875 --> 00:04:56.000
<i>Wow. Someone really</i>
<i>screwed the pooch on that one.</i>

98
00:04:56.083 --> 00:04:57.458
<i>Yeah. that's for sure.</i>

99
00:04:57.541 --> 00:04:59.666
<i>Technical mistakes</i>
<i>can be very enlightening.</i>

100
00:04:59.750 --> 00:05:04.166
<i>I heard that there are several petitions</i>
<i>now calling for her to step down.</i>

101
00:05:04.250 --> 00:05:05.083
{\an8}<i>Mm. As she should.</i>

102
00:05:05.166 --> 00:05:06.166
{\an8}SHOULD BRANDMEIER RESIGN?

103
00:05:06.250 --> 00:05:08.000
{\an8}<i>As she should. Or not?</i>
<i>Tell us what you think.</i>

104
00:05:08.083 --> 00:05:09.291
It's completely unfair.

105
00:05:09.375 --> 00:05:12.791
The finance minister just said
unemployment is like athletes foot.

106
00:05:12.875 --> 00:05:14.791
- This must be…
- You already know how this works.

107
00:05:14.875 --> 00:05:18.666
Women working in politics are held to
a completely different standard than men.

108
00:05:20.291 --> 00:05:23.875
Here. With this.
you'll be totally incognito in Tyrol.

109
00:05:27.416 --> 00:05:29.375
Wear it. And now it's time to leave.

110
00:05:33.208 --> 00:05:34.458
Ugh…

111
00:05:36.666 --> 00:05:38.125
That's my favorite pillow!

112
00:05:39.708 --> 00:05:42.166
Torsten. not so fast!

113
00:05:42.250 --> 00:05:44.125
Torsten. stop. stop. stop. stop!

114
00:05:44.208 --> 00:05:46.291
It's not a race. Torsten! Torsten!

115
00:05:46.375 --> 00:05:49.041
Hey. control that animal!

116
00:05:49.125 --> 00:05:50.750
Your career is at stake. Ursula.

117
00:05:50.833 --> 00:05:53.875
So keep your mouth shut and
make sure no one recognizes you.

118
00:05:55.208 --> 00:05:56.208
Good luck.

119
00:05:58.833 --> 00:06:00.541
PDT: THE ANIMAL-FRIENDLY PARTY

120
00:06:02.041 --> 00:06:03.416
OUR DOG HATER FOR EUROPE

121
00:06:19.416 --> 00:06:23.000
ZILLERTAL RAILWAY

122
00:06:44.291 --> 00:06:45.958
Oh. that's great.

123
00:06:46.041 --> 00:06:49.000
We're spending the weekend
with a killer and his charming owner.

124
00:06:49.750 --> 00:06:50.875
Wow!

125
00:06:52.916 --> 00:06:54.708
Are you here for the dog training?

126
00:06:54.791 --> 00:06:55.916
- Yeah. and you?
- Mm-hmm.

127
00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:56.916
This is unbelievable!

128
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.250
It is so gorgeous up here.

129
00:07:01.916 --> 00:07:03.625
Oh…

130
00:07:04.333 --> 00:07:05.750
Thank you. that's very kind.

131
00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.416
I hear that Nodon lives somewhere up there

132
00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:16.333
- in those mountains.
- <i>Hey.</i>

133
00:07:16.416 --> 00:07:18.416
Why didn't you arrange
for a private session?

134
00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:19.916
There are way too many people.

135
00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:24.250
<i>He doesn't offer private classes.</i>
<i>And he's booked for the next four months.</i>

136
00:07:24.333 --> 00:07:26.583
<i>You're lucky I found someone</i>
<i>willing to sell their spot.</i>

137
00:07:26.666 --> 00:07:28.125
Go find anyone else to be here.

138
00:07:28.208 --> 00:07:31.208
Get someone to train this insane beast
and give him back to me fixed.

139
00:07:31.291 --> 00:07:34.541
<i>That's not how it works.</i>
<i>You have to learn how to deal with her.</i>

140
00:07:34.625 --> 00:07:38.000
- Nodon!
- <i>The guy is a genius with dogs.</i>

141
00:07:38.083 --> 00:07:40.208
We're coming!

142
00:07:40.291 --> 00:07:42.041
Oh God. they're all totally nuts.

143
00:07:42.125 --> 00:07:43.791
<i>That's why the dogs are being trained.</i>

144
00:07:43.875 --> 00:07:45.750
I mean the humans.

145
00:07:45.833 --> 00:07:48.250
<i>Pull yourself together.</i>
<i>At the next </i>Live on Wednesday.

146
00:07:48.333 --> 00:07:50.500
<i>- you'll present yourself as a dog lover.</i>
- Hello!

147
00:07:50.583 --> 00:07:52.708
- Call me Gustl.
- <i>You two'll be soulmates by then.</i>

148
00:07:52.791 --> 00:07:54.708
<i>- You need to take this very seriously.</i>
- Uh. hello.

149
00:07:54.791 --> 00:07:58.958
<i>After the recent incident.</i>
<i>91% of viewers voted for your resignation.</i>

150
00:07:59.041 --> 00:08:00.875
So you are here to see Nodon?

151
00:08:00.958 --> 00:08:02.500
Uh. yeah. yeah.

152
00:08:02.583 --> 00:08:04.666
- Yeah.
<i>- Stay incognito. If you're recognized.</i>

153
00:08:04.750 --> 00:08:06.916
<i>- it's over.</i>
- Okay! Ladies and gentlemen.

154
00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:08.333
I'm tired of waiting. Come on.

155
00:08:14.250 --> 00:08:15.791
In that death trap?

156
00:08:16.750 --> 00:08:18.291
You prefer to walk?

157
00:08:18.375 --> 00:08:19.500
REISINGER INN

158
00:08:21.958 --> 00:08:23.958
Okay. ladies and gentlemen.

159
00:08:31.208 --> 00:08:32.458
Oh my!

160
00:08:37.500 --> 00:08:39.291
This can't be happening.

161
00:08:51.958 --> 00:08:53.791
Shh…

162
00:09:01.458 --> 00:09:03.791
So this little beauty is Lady Gaga.

163
00:09:03.875 --> 00:09:06.583
Gaga. or G. depending on her mood.

164
00:09:06.666 --> 00:09:07.916
And my name is Ziggy.

165
00:09:08.500 --> 00:09:10.458
And this is my husband. Helmut.

166
00:09:10.541 --> 00:09:12.708
He's a professor
of 19th Century Literature.

167
00:09:14.250 --> 00:09:16.125
Gaga and my man
have problems with each other.

168
00:09:16.833 --> 00:09:20.583
I have no problem with that dog.
That dog has a problem with me.

169
00:09:20.666 --> 00:09:23.583
Helmut is part of the problem.
Plus. he's on the spectrum.

170
00:09:24.791 --> 00:09:26.958
On the spectrum? Did I miss something?

171
00:09:27.791 --> 00:09:29.583
Like maybe a professional diagnosis?

172
00:09:29.666 --> 00:09:31.541
It's more like an observation.
Don't freak out.

173
00:09:31.625 --> 00:09:35.125
An observation. you say?
Well. isn't that great?

174
00:09:35.208 --> 00:09:37.416
Any other observations you want to share?

175
00:09:37.500 --> 00:09:40.875
Something we can all discuss
in this termite-ridden carriage?

176
00:09:43.166 --> 00:09:45.666
Hi! This is Torsten!

177
00:09:47.625 --> 00:09:50.541
- Yeah. and. uh. I'm. uh. Babs.
- Mm.

178
00:09:50.625 --> 00:09:52.708
Also. my problem is…

179
00:09:52.791 --> 00:09:54.333
um…

180
00:09:54.416 --> 00:09:57.833
that I might have to give up Torsten.
because he's so wild.

181
00:09:57.916 --> 00:09:59.166
But he's also friendly!

182
00:09:59.250 --> 00:10:02.458
And when he hurts people.
he doesn't really mean it. just… you know.

183
00:10:03.125 --> 00:10:05.833
Were there lawsuits?
Sure. but he's a sweet boy.

184
00:10:05.916 --> 00:10:09.125
We've tried different trainers.
but none have fixed the problem.

185
00:10:09.208 --> 00:10:10.791
I mean. we've done a lot of classes.

186
00:10:12.041 --> 00:10:13.041
Good boy.

187
00:10:14.291 --> 00:10:16.875
Um. do you have a heart-wrenching story

188
00:10:16.958 --> 00:10:18.875
you'd like to share
with your new best friends?

189
00:10:18.958 --> 00:10:20.625
- No.
- Thank you.

190
00:10:25.291 --> 00:10:27.208
And what about you then? What's your name?

191
00:10:27.291 --> 00:10:28.125
Ur…

192
00:10:28.875 --> 00:10:29.833
schi.

193
00:10:30.708 --> 00:10:31.833
Urschi?

194
00:10:32.458 --> 00:10:33.875
Your name is great!

195
00:10:34.375 --> 00:10:37.041
It's… It's a very nice name.

196
00:10:37.125 --> 00:10:40.333
It's fine. I'm not on this trip
to make new friends.

197
00:10:46.541 --> 00:10:48.958
Hello. my name is Torsten.

198
00:10:49.041 --> 00:10:51.083
Would you like to be friends with me?

199
00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:57.791
Oh wow. look what a sweetheart you are!

200
00:10:59.875 --> 00:11:01.041
Hi. the name's Babs.

201
00:11:01.625 --> 00:11:02.791
Hakan.

202
00:11:02.875 --> 00:11:04.250
And who is this friend?

203
00:11:04.833 --> 00:11:05.791
Roxy.

204
00:11:05.875 --> 00:11:07.333
What's with the muzzle?

205
00:11:07.416 --> 00:11:09.125
Maybe she talks too much.

206
00:11:10.208 --> 00:11:11.125
Stop it.

207
00:11:11.208 --> 00:11:12.833
Mm.

208
00:11:12.916 --> 00:11:15.166
Hey. Gaga.

209
00:11:15.750 --> 00:11:17.875
Hey. look what Daddy has for you.

210
00:11:18.958 --> 00:11:20.625
- Shh!
- Gaga.

211
00:11:20.708 --> 00:11:21.958
Look here.

212
00:11:22.041 --> 00:11:23.000
Gaga.

213
00:11:23.083 --> 00:11:25.000
It's okay. you're okay.

214
00:11:25.083 --> 00:11:27.375
Good girl. Here.

215
00:11:27.458 --> 00:11:31.250
This is Gaga's emotional support animal.
It helps with her stress.

216
00:11:33.625 --> 00:11:35.875
- Sorry. Ziggy. was it? One sec.
- Hey!

217
00:11:39.750 --> 00:11:41.541
Well. that wasn't very nice.

218
00:11:41.625 --> 00:11:44.583
It could be worse. at least he didn't
throw the dog over the side.

219
00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:00.625
My God. this is so cheesy.

220
00:12:02.333 --> 00:12:03.458
Yah!

221
00:12:14.833 --> 00:12:19.375
Ziggy. I'm interested in
how you got to that spectrum comment.

222
00:12:19.458 --> 00:12:22.291
You know I'm not the only one.
Sabine believes it.

223
00:12:22.375 --> 00:12:24.541
Oh! Your therapist is diagnosing me now?

224
00:12:24.625 --> 00:12:27.750
When? When was that?
Did she diagnose me remotely?

225
00:12:27.833 --> 00:12:30.125
I said you could join me
in therapy but you refused.

226
00:12:30.208 --> 00:12:32.208
At least I'll be dead soon.

227
00:12:32.291 --> 00:12:33.875
Oh my God.

228
00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:36.875
I hope that's him.

229
00:13:26.291 --> 00:13:27.208
Uh…

230
00:13:50.625 --> 00:13:52.375
- Well. put her down!
- Yeah.

231
00:14:10.250 --> 00:14:12.625
Now that I've met your companions.

232
00:14:13.125 --> 00:14:14.958
it's time for us
to learn about each other.

233
00:14:15.041 --> 00:14:17.375
Yeah. but please. no sniffing. young man.

234
00:14:17.458 --> 00:14:18.708
I'm fine with it.

235
00:14:18.791 --> 00:14:21.458
No worries. I only do that with the dogs.

236
00:14:22.041 --> 00:14:26.166
It's a method I learned when I lived with
a pack of wolves out in the wilderness.

237
00:14:29.250 --> 00:14:32.833
That's cool. That is really brave.

238
00:14:33.375 --> 00:14:35.125
Or really stupid.

239
00:14:37.958 --> 00:14:40.666
This is Heidi. I am her dagda.

240
00:14:41.541 --> 00:14:42.583
My name is Nodon.

241
00:14:43.416 --> 00:14:45.416
- He's a what?
- A dagda.

242
00:14:45.500 --> 00:14:46.916
"Dagda" is a Celtic word.

243
00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:49.458
It means "Companion

244
00:14:49.541 --> 00:14:51.583
and protector of dogs."

245
00:14:52.750 --> 00:14:54.000
Please take their leashes off.

246
00:14:55.416 --> 00:14:57.916
Um… I'd. um. love that.

247
00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:00.541
um. but I'm afraid that he'll run away
if I let him off the leash.

248
00:15:01.166 --> 00:15:02.416
No.

249
00:15:03.833 --> 00:15:04.833
Okay.

250
00:15:07.375 --> 00:15:09.708
Here. my love.

251
00:15:24.291 --> 00:15:26.833
The stories were true! It's real!

252
00:15:27.416 --> 00:15:29.458
He has magical powers!

253
00:15:33.125 --> 00:15:36.125
- Can you take off the muzzle?
- Nobody wants that.

254
00:15:36.208 --> 00:15:38.666
He's right. none of us want
to see that dog without a muzzle.

255
00:15:38.750 --> 00:15:39.916
I'm attached to my face.

256
00:15:40.750 --> 00:15:41.916
Great.

257
00:15:42.416 --> 00:15:44.083
Okay. that's fine. You're not ready.

258
00:15:47.708 --> 00:15:49.041
And the dress. please.

259
00:15:49.125 --> 00:15:51.708
But Gaga loves her dress.
It gives her self-confidence.

260
00:15:52.291 --> 00:15:54.458
Oh please. Well…

261
00:15:56.833 --> 00:15:58.500
Oh my God.

262
00:15:58.583 --> 00:15:59.666
What'd you do?

263
00:16:08.458 --> 00:16:09.666
Gaga!

264
00:16:13.000 --> 00:16:15.583
Oh God. Gaga's a city girl.
She'll never find her way back.

265
00:16:16.166 --> 00:16:17.833
She'll be eaten by a squirrel!

266
00:16:17.916 --> 00:16:22.083
Okay. people. I'd like these returned
in pristine condition. understand?

267
00:16:22.666 --> 00:16:24.500
This is Birgit.

268
00:16:24.583 --> 00:16:25.916
She's your host.

269
00:16:26.625 --> 00:16:28.708
and the heart and soul of this house.

270
00:16:29.916 --> 00:16:31.416
We're going hiking.

271
00:16:31.500 --> 00:16:32.583
No chance in hell.

272
00:16:32.666 --> 00:16:35.416
I've been traveling for seven hours.
I'm ready for a nap.

273
00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:38.333
A nap. then a cocktail.
My room key. please.

274
00:16:41.625 --> 00:16:43.125
What is this?

275
00:16:45.041 --> 00:16:47.208
Everyone put on your hiking boots.

276
00:16:51.500 --> 00:16:52.750
If anything bad happens to Gaga.

277
00:16:52.833 --> 00:16:54.041
- I'll kill him.
- Hm.

278
00:16:54.125 --> 00:16:56.291
I see your little power play.

279
00:17:00.416 --> 00:17:02.875
It's time to surrender your cell phones.

280
00:17:14.333 --> 00:17:17.291
We want you to focus completely
on your surroundings.

281
00:17:17.375 --> 00:17:20.000
Yeah. I'm fully committed.

282
00:17:20.583 --> 00:17:23.583
We can't leave
before I get all of your phones.

283
00:17:25.083 --> 00:17:28.458
You can give them up voluntarily.
or I can remove them from you.

284
00:17:28.541 --> 00:17:30.458
Oh…

285
00:17:44.333 --> 00:17:46.375
Everything was perfect.

286
00:17:46.458 --> 00:17:49.000
Gaga made us
a complete family. full of love.

287
00:17:49.083 --> 00:17:51.125
But then she started to bite Helmut.

288
00:17:51.208 --> 00:17:53.291
So what did you do then?

289
00:17:54.708 --> 00:17:56.291
What did I do? Gaga likes me.

290
00:17:59.250 --> 00:18:00.250
So?

291
00:18:00.750 --> 00:18:01.958
What's my option?

292
00:18:03.041 --> 00:18:05.625
We take a rest. up on that hill.

293
00:18:08.541 --> 00:18:10.416
This is the land of our Celtic ancestors.

294
00:18:11.083 --> 00:18:14.875
That's not true.
My people are all from Hamburg-Blankenese.

295
00:18:14.958 --> 00:18:17.875
We will immerse ourselves
in their teachings.

296
00:18:17.958 --> 00:18:21.666
They were extremely knowledgeable
about nature. living creatures.

297
00:18:21.750 --> 00:18:23.750
and especially dogs.

298
00:18:25.291 --> 00:18:26.750
Which way. Legolas?

299
00:18:28.333 --> 00:18:29.333
Ugh.

300
00:18:31.875 --> 00:18:35.583
She's only forgetting your name.
Nodon. as it's a bit different.

301
00:18:35.666 --> 00:18:38.291
I mean. it is kind of an unusual name.

302
00:18:38.833 --> 00:18:40.541
I'm named after Nodons.

303
00:18:40.625 --> 00:18:42.125
He's the Celtic god of dogs.

304
00:18:42.708 --> 00:18:43.916
Ah.

305
00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:46.458
Do you mean there really is a god of dogs?

306
00:18:46.541 --> 00:18:47.541
Yeah.

307
00:18:48.208 --> 00:18:50.500
Oh wow. I can tell.

308
00:18:51.750 --> 00:18:53.541
Okay. look. I have to be honest…

309
00:18:53.625 --> 00:18:56.208
I know you're not a real god.

310
00:18:56.291 --> 00:18:59.166
Please. I'm not stupid.

311
00:19:01.416 --> 00:19:03.125
But for me and for Torsten.

312
00:19:03.958 --> 00:19:05.458
can you please be a real god?

313
00:19:05.541 --> 00:19:07.833
I can't fail this exam again.

314
00:19:07.916 --> 00:19:10.125
If they take Torsten.
I'm not sure I'm gonna survive.

315
00:19:10.208 --> 00:19:12.333
We'll make sure that you both succeed.

316
00:19:23.333 --> 00:19:24.750
Look around.

317
00:19:26.250 --> 00:19:28.625
Take in the magic of this view.

318
00:19:35.708 --> 00:19:38.875
The very first step in becoming
a better partner for your dogs…

319
00:19:40.250 --> 00:19:43.375
is to shake off
all the stress of your daily grind

320
00:19:43.458 --> 00:19:45.083
and leave it all behind.

321
00:19:45.833 --> 00:19:47.708
Just like the Celts would do.

322
00:19:49.583 --> 00:19:50.916
Now breathe deeply.

323
00:19:53.500 --> 00:19:54.500
And out.

324
00:19:57.041 --> 00:19:59.583
And with each exhale…

325
00:19:59.666 --> 00:20:02.375
…let all your negative energy float away.

326
00:20:04.500 --> 00:20:06.625
Cleanse yourselves
of what's weighing you down.

327
00:20:10.833 --> 00:20:12.208
In.

328
00:20:12.291 --> 00:20:13.750
And out.

329
00:20:13.833 --> 00:20:15.250
And in.

330
00:20:15.333 --> 00:20:16.791
And out.

331
00:20:19.500 --> 00:20:21.458
- And?
- And what?

332
00:20:22.208 --> 00:20:24.875
The breathing. Relaxing. Unspooling.

333
00:20:24.958 --> 00:20:26.583
Yeah. cool.

334
00:20:27.458 --> 00:20:29.666
Fine for them.
but that's not why I'm here.

335
00:20:29.750 --> 00:20:30.833
I want a hamburger.

336
00:20:31.500 --> 00:20:32.833
In your backpack.

337
00:20:35.125 --> 00:20:36.125
In.

338
00:20:36.666 --> 00:20:38.291
And out.

339
00:20:38.375 --> 00:20:39.750
In.

340
00:20:40.458 --> 00:20:42.083
And out.

341
00:20:42.791 --> 00:20:44.916
Are you kidding me?

342
00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:46.666
There are no sandwiches or burgers?

343
00:20:46.750 --> 00:20:47.625
No fruit?

344
00:20:49.416 --> 00:20:51.750
You will find in the backpack
all that you need.

345
00:20:52.333 --> 00:20:55.833
Things… that you can only find in nature.

346
00:20:55.916 --> 00:20:57.583
So nature has a sense of humor.

347
00:20:57.666 --> 00:21:00.125
This is just the forest floor.
nothing else.

348
00:21:01.000 --> 00:21:03.500
Did you gather these
herbs all by yourself?

349
00:21:03.583 --> 00:21:07.291
Oh yes. it's collected.
it's dried. it's roasted…

350
00:21:08.208 --> 00:21:10.916
and much of it was found
just this very morning.

351
00:21:13.791 --> 00:21:16.833
It's still a mystery
why you chose this bizarre man for us.

352
00:21:17.375 --> 00:21:19.500
Was it maybe due to his appearance?

353
00:21:19.583 --> 00:21:22.041
- Oh Helmut.
- I'm not very happy with your choice.

354
00:21:22.125 --> 00:21:23.375
Not a shock.

355
00:21:23.458 --> 00:21:25.500
As usual. it's all my fault.
You win again.

356
00:21:26.291 --> 00:21:28.000
Is this the prize for winning?

357
00:21:28.541 --> 00:21:31.833
So. Nodon. will you also
stay at the inn with us and our dogs?

358
00:21:31.916 --> 00:21:32.916
No.

359
00:21:33.708 --> 00:21:34.875
I live over there.

360
00:21:34.958 --> 00:21:37.041
on that ridge. surrounded by nature.

361
00:21:37.125 --> 00:21:38.625
Really?

362
00:21:38.708 --> 00:21:39.583
Mm-hmm.

363
00:21:40.083 --> 00:21:41.375
All alone?

364
00:21:42.166 --> 00:21:43.458
Yep.

365
00:21:43.541 --> 00:21:47.708
How about all of us go up there
on a hike or something?

366
00:21:48.375 --> 00:21:49.541
To visit you!

367
00:21:50.125 --> 00:21:51.958
No.

368
00:21:52.583 --> 00:21:53.791
Okay.

369
00:21:55.541 --> 00:21:56.875
So tell me. Hakan.

370
00:21:57.625 --> 00:22:00.000
what's your story? What brings you here?

371
00:22:01.125 --> 00:22:04.166
- My wife made me.
- Share more about yourself?

372
00:22:04.250 --> 00:22:06.500
This isn't about me.
my dog is the problem.

373
00:22:07.875 --> 00:22:09.250
What is this?

374
00:22:10.750 --> 00:22:12.125
It's a bird's egg.

375
00:22:12.791 --> 00:22:14.041
It fell out of its nest.

376
00:22:14.125 --> 00:22:15.875
So what should I do with it?

377
00:22:15.958 --> 00:22:17.250
Should I incubate it?

378
00:22:17.833 --> 00:22:19.500
- Eat it.
- Is it cooked?

379
00:22:19.583 --> 00:22:23.750
No. You slurp it raw.
Some find it a delicacy.

380
00:22:24.666 --> 00:22:26.791
So gross. Mm.

381
00:22:27.458 --> 00:22:28.375
Hm.

382
00:22:28.458 --> 00:22:29.791
Anyone want a Celtic treat?

383
00:22:29.875 --> 00:22:31.416
No. thanks.

384
00:22:46.708 --> 00:22:47.541
Ugh.

385
00:22:53.666 --> 00:22:55.166
I'm sure that by now.

386
00:22:56.041 --> 00:22:59.458
most of you will have noticed
an aura around you.

387
00:23:01.708 --> 00:23:04.041
We are at an important Celtic place.

388
00:23:04.875 --> 00:23:07.166
Feel the power of that energy.

389
00:23:08.750 --> 00:23:09.750
I feel it.

390
00:23:10.375 --> 00:23:12.416
My spirit place is a stylish hotel bar.

391
00:23:12.500 --> 00:23:15.916
with a martini and a club sandwich.

392
00:23:22.583 --> 00:23:24.291
Torsten!

393
00:23:26.333 --> 00:23:27.625
Yeah. hello!

394
00:23:27.708 --> 00:23:30.666
Oh hi. my princess. hello.

395
00:23:30.750 --> 00:23:32.750
Did you miss your daddy?

396
00:23:32.833 --> 00:23:35.875
Were you all alone
in that terrifying forest? Mm?

397
00:23:35.958 --> 00:23:38.166
She was in the meadow
with all the other dogs.

398
00:23:38.250 --> 00:23:40.083
She finally got
to stretch her muscles again.

399
00:23:40.750 --> 00:23:41.666
Mm.

400
00:23:43.166 --> 00:23:45.166
Hey. uptight one!

401
00:23:45.708 --> 00:23:47.666
Don't forget to take your friend.

402
00:23:47.750 --> 00:23:50.458
- She sleeps with me. not somewhere else?
- Yeah.

403
00:23:50.541 --> 00:23:52.333
- Can she sleep with you?
- No.

404
00:23:53.125 --> 00:23:55.416
Are you sure? I can pay.

405
00:23:56.333 --> 00:23:58.000
What time do we eat?

406
00:23:59.291 --> 00:24:00.500
It's in the brochure.

407
00:24:02.750 --> 00:24:04.875
Our day together
was extremely spiritual for me.

408
00:24:04.958 --> 00:24:06.166
Ugh. Come on.

409
00:24:06.250 --> 00:24:08.083
Thank you all so much.

410
00:24:08.166 --> 00:24:10.625
No. We thank <i>you.</i>

411
00:24:10.708 --> 00:24:13.458
Tomorrow we shall all meet up
with our dogs.

412
00:24:13.541 --> 00:24:14.875
9:00 a.m. at the lake.

413
00:24:14.958 --> 00:24:16.041
Um. what?

414
00:24:16.125 --> 00:24:17.500
Yeah. Gustl will bring you.

415
00:24:28.166 --> 00:24:30.375
"REISINGER INN" REQUIRES
A WPA2/WPA3 PASSWORD.

416
00:24:33.250 --> 00:24:34.666
Okay.

417
00:24:41.291 --> 00:24:42.458
INCORRECT PASSWORD

418
00:24:45.500 --> 00:24:46.708
Ah.

419
00:24:48.875 --> 00:24:49.875
Off.

420
00:24:53.458 --> 00:24:54.750
Off.

421
00:25:08.791 --> 00:25:12.916
Hmm. I miss something new?
Is it banquet night?

422
00:25:17.958 --> 00:25:20.125
- Where's Brenda?
- In my room.

423
00:25:20.208 --> 00:25:21.166
Alone?

424
00:25:21.250 --> 00:25:24.541
Of course! She doesn't need my help
slobbering on my things.

425
00:25:25.875 --> 00:25:28.250
What? I'm busy.

426
00:25:28.833 --> 00:25:32.500
Um. I'd like my phone returned.
and the password for the Wi-Fi. please.

427
00:25:32.583 --> 00:25:35.000
I'm not here on vacation. I have to work.

428
00:25:35.083 --> 00:25:37.291
A working woman. eh? So am I.

429
00:25:37.375 --> 00:25:38.833
Should we talk business?

430
00:25:39.458 --> 00:25:41.541
No. thanks. My phone. please.

431
00:25:42.583 --> 00:25:46.375
Fine. If you don't place an order.
you can eat dog food.

432
00:25:46.458 --> 00:25:48.250
Wait! Mm…

433
00:25:49.250 --> 00:25:52.750
Do you have anything to drink?
Like a bottle of red wine?

434
00:25:52.833 --> 00:25:54.583
You think we're barbarians here?

435
00:25:54.666 --> 00:25:57.750
- We're in Tyrol. we have the best wines.
- Oh yeah?

436
00:25:57.833 --> 00:26:00.083
Or a Vernatsch from Lake Kaltern?

437
00:26:00.583 --> 00:26:03.958
Annoying as hell. but the woman has taste.

438
00:26:06.083 --> 00:26:07.708
So. it's my time.

439
00:26:07.791 --> 00:26:09.875
- No. Ziggy. not now. please don't.
- No.

440
00:26:21.500 --> 00:26:23.000
Here you go. ma'am.

441
00:26:27.166 --> 00:26:31.791
Uh. Birgit. would you like to see
my collection of handmade scented candles?

442
00:26:31.875 --> 00:26:34.208
This is Salty Sea Breeze.
and Caribbean Coco.

443
00:26:34.291 --> 00:26:36.208
which would be fantastic in this abode.

444
00:26:36.291 --> 00:26:38.458
Caribbean?

445
00:26:40.000 --> 00:26:41.916
That would be original.

446
00:26:44.000 --> 00:26:46.458
Please take your scented candles
and put them away.

447
00:26:48.166 --> 00:26:51.125
- Good evening. everyone!
- Evening.

448
00:26:51.208 --> 00:26:52.541
Ah!

449
00:26:52.625 --> 00:26:54.791
That's amazing! Are they all hand-made?

450
00:26:54.875 --> 00:26:57.291
So. I usually sell to wholesale customers.

451
00:26:57.375 --> 00:27:00.250
but if you're interested.
I'll make an exception just for you.

452
00:27:00.333 --> 00:27:01.416
- Really?
- Mm.

453
00:27:02.583 --> 00:27:03.541
Mm!

454
00:27:03.625 --> 00:27:06.916
Coconut? Torsten loves coconut.

455
00:27:07.000 --> 00:27:09.750
He once ate an entire coconut
in two bites. He's a big fan.

456
00:27:09.833 --> 00:27:12.458
This is an excellent choice. my dear.

457
00:27:12.541 --> 00:27:13.916
That'll be 20 euros. please.

458
00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:16.375
Ah. you are saving my butt.

459
00:27:16.458 --> 00:27:19.791
It's because I forgot
Torsten's aroma lamp at my place.

460
00:27:23.166 --> 00:27:25.541
Mm! I'm so hungry.

461
00:27:25.625 --> 00:27:26.875
Why is that?

462
00:27:26.958 --> 00:27:30.583
I gave you an extra-large portion
of berries and mushrooms.

463
00:27:30.666 --> 00:27:31.791
Mm.

464
00:27:31.875 --> 00:27:33.750
And a bird's egg. Extra large.

465
00:27:35.958 --> 00:27:39.250
That was for
the arrogant heifer from the city.

466
00:27:40.000 --> 00:27:41.458
She passed on it.

467
00:27:41.958 --> 00:27:44.333
And as a real Celt.
I'm supposed to eat it all.

468
00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:51.875
The first serving is.
of course. for you. So.

469
00:27:53.000 --> 00:27:54.833
- Mm.
- Enjoy. sweetie.

470
00:27:54.916 --> 00:27:56.291
- Thanks. Birgit.
- Mm-hmm.

471
00:27:56.375 --> 00:27:57.375
Mm.

472
00:27:59.166 --> 00:28:04.500
So. Simon. why make it so hard
for yourself with all this Celtic crap?

473
00:28:04.583 --> 00:28:07.208
You know very well that people pay extra
when you give them a show.

474
00:28:07.291 --> 00:28:09.791
- Plus. we need the money.
- But you take it way too far.

475
00:28:09.875 --> 00:28:12.708
We are Tyroleans.
and there's pride in that.

476
00:28:13.208 --> 00:28:14.208
Mm.

477
00:28:15.458 --> 00:28:18.416
Birgit. a Tyrolean dog trainer
is not special at all.

478
00:28:18.500 --> 00:28:21.208
But a Celt. that's something mystical

479
00:28:21.291 --> 00:28:22.875
that has… That has flair.

480
00:28:22.958 --> 00:28:26.500
Flair. flair. flair.
That's just a load of poppycock.

481
00:28:26.583 --> 00:28:27.750
I'm a believer.

482
00:28:28.250 --> 00:28:31.375
Since it's Nodon instead of me.
we've become huge.

483
00:28:31.916 --> 00:28:33.833
Even Bill Kaulitz signed up for this.

484
00:28:33.916 --> 00:28:35.166
Who is Bill Kaulitz?

485
00:28:40.375 --> 00:28:41.458
I don't know him.

486
00:28:41.541 --> 00:28:42.791
- Really?
- No idea.

487
00:28:45.416 --> 00:28:47.416
Mm!

488
00:28:48.125 --> 00:28:49.958
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

489
00:28:50.833 --> 00:28:53.291
- This is for you.
- Thank you.

490
00:28:56.083 --> 00:28:57.083
Thanks.

491
00:28:57.875 --> 00:28:59.625
You. Where are you going?

492
00:28:59.708 --> 00:29:01.458
We're not some snack bar.

493
00:29:01.541 --> 00:29:04.000
In Tyrol. you sit at a table.
like a person.

494
00:29:04.583 --> 00:29:07.375
- Uh-huh.
- Yeah. Hakan. Stay here with us.

495
00:29:07.458 --> 00:29:09.458
It's so much nicer
than sitting by yourself alone.

496
00:29:10.750 --> 00:29:12.750
No. It's not.

497
00:29:13.625 --> 00:29:15.875
Have you ever met anyone
as mean as that guy?

498
00:29:15.958 --> 00:29:17.083
I'm not a fan.

499
00:29:17.166 --> 00:29:19.250
He tossed Gaga's favorite toy
off of the truck.

500
00:29:19.916 --> 00:29:21.125
I hope he's not a murderer.

501
00:29:21.750 --> 00:29:24.208
Which is why
my phone and I need to reunite.

502
00:29:24.291 --> 00:29:25.333
Enjoy.

503
00:29:25.416 --> 00:29:26.541
Thanks.

504
00:29:30.041 --> 00:29:30.916
Oh!

505
00:29:32.625 --> 00:29:34.041
Bon appétit.

506
00:29:34.125 --> 00:29:36.083
Torsten.

507
00:29:38.666 --> 00:29:39.625
Mm.

508
00:29:39.708 --> 00:29:41.666
Oh. look at that.

509
00:29:41.750 --> 00:29:43.333
Gaga's ready for the Met Gala.

510
00:29:43.416 --> 00:29:46.375
It's a one-of-a-kind. A dog needs
to feel just as special as we do.

511
00:29:46.458 --> 00:29:48.458
- Wow.
- And I paid for it.

512
00:29:52.708 --> 00:29:54.250
- Ziggy.
- Hm?

513
00:29:54.333 --> 00:29:56.541
Probably
in our best interest to ignore this.

514
00:30:02.666 --> 00:30:04.541
Oh my. I'm so sorry.

515
00:30:05.208 --> 00:30:06.750
Listen. your dog is messed up.

516
00:30:07.458 --> 00:30:10.958
You think hippie Legolas is gonna fix
your disturbed furball in two days?

517
00:30:18.708 --> 00:30:20.708
Um. okay. um…

518
00:30:22.416 --> 00:30:23.916
I need to leave now.

519
00:30:25.166 --> 00:30:26.041
Torsten.

520
00:30:26.625 --> 00:30:27.708
Let's go.

521
00:30:30.291 --> 00:30:32.375
- That wasn't kind.
- Yeah.

522
00:30:34.500 --> 00:30:36.166
We should all be kinder.

523
00:30:38.083 --> 00:30:39.125
So I'm the pariah now?

524
00:30:39.208 --> 00:30:40.458
Not to me.

525
00:30:41.041 --> 00:30:41.916
I see.

526
00:30:43.708 --> 00:30:47.375
I have this feeling
that we've met and we know each other.

527
00:30:48.916 --> 00:30:50.166
- We have not.
- Hm?

528
00:30:50.250 --> 00:30:51.666
Mm. mm.

529
00:30:51.750 --> 00:30:53.250
I am good with remembering faces.

530
00:30:53.958 --> 00:30:56.958
And I'd remember
a distinguished professor of literature.

531
00:30:57.041 --> 00:30:58.125
You're so important.

532
00:31:35.750 --> 00:31:39.750
Yeah. So. where is our Celtic master?

533
00:31:54.208 --> 00:31:57.416
<i>Whoa. oh-oh</i>

534
00:32:03.208 --> 00:32:04.416
Good morning. dear dagdas.

535
00:32:04.500 --> 00:32:06.166
Good morning.

536
00:32:06.250 --> 00:32:08.791
I start the day with a refreshing swim
in this humble lake.

537
00:32:09.458 --> 00:32:10.458
Yeah. sure.

538
00:32:11.000 --> 00:32:14.041
It gets the blood flowing.
Cleanses the soul.

539
00:32:14.125 --> 00:32:15.791
Everyone should try it! Who's first?

540
00:32:19.250 --> 00:32:20.833
So.

541
00:32:20.916 --> 00:32:24.333
Today I'll see how you work
with your protegees as teammates.

542
00:32:25.041 --> 00:32:26.291
We're gonna beat everyone.

543
00:32:27.166 --> 00:32:28.625
It's not against other people.

544
00:32:29.291 --> 00:32:30.333
Mm.

545
00:32:31.291 --> 00:32:32.916
This is how we will proceed.

546
00:32:33.416 --> 00:32:35.958
Helmut. you're the master of Gaga today.

547
00:32:36.041 --> 00:32:38.583
Ziggy. put her down. please.
and give Helmut the leash.

548
00:32:38.666 --> 00:32:40.291
Now listen. Nodon.
this is not a good idea.

549
00:32:40.375 --> 00:32:43.833
You see. um. Gaga and I.
we are both. I should say…

550
00:32:43.916 --> 00:32:45.250
We're dysfunctional.

551
00:32:48.208 --> 00:32:50.041
You'll be all right. darling.

552
00:32:52.541 --> 00:32:54.083
You bear the responsibility today.

553
00:32:57.458 --> 00:32:59.541
Ziggy. keep out of Gaga's sight. okay?

554
00:33:00.708 --> 00:33:02.333
- I'm sorry. love.
- You're not sorry.

555
00:33:02.416 --> 00:33:04.916
- Oh. you think this is my idea?
- This is part of your plan.

556
00:33:08.750 --> 00:33:11.041
Look… I don't mean to complain.

557
00:33:11.125 --> 00:33:12.583
but I paid for dog training.

558
00:33:12.666 --> 00:33:15.708
and all I'm getting
is a walkabout in the wild.

559
00:33:17.333 --> 00:33:19.000
This stupid dog doesn't get it.

560
00:33:20.083 --> 00:33:23.041
- Let positive energy flow through you.
- Hm.

561
00:33:23.125 --> 00:33:26.958
Be a great dagda.
and your enemy becomes a friend.

562
00:33:27.041 --> 00:33:29.083
when you make your friendship a priority.

563
00:33:30.958 --> 00:33:33.208
Yeah. well. I didn't need
to trudge through some forest

564
00:33:33.291 --> 00:33:35.208
for this stupid fortune cookie wisdom.

565
00:33:35.291 --> 00:33:38.458
You could've shared this via e-mail.
WhatsApp. SMS. fax machine.

566
00:33:38.541 --> 00:33:39.708
or whatever you Celts use.

567
00:33:39.791 --> 00:33:41.000
Snapchat.

568
00:33:41.708 --> 00:33:44.041
Tell me when
we're going to start dog training.

569
00:33:45.291 --> 00:33:46.583
I don't train dogs.

570
00:33:47.958 --> 00:33:48.916
I train humans.

571
00:33:50.916 --> 00:33:53.333
<i>Way back</i>
<i>Played them games on you</i>

572
00:33:53.416 --> 00:33:56.416
<i>Knew that I was wrong</i>
<i>'Cause now I'm sittin' on</i>

573
00:33:56.500 --> 00:33:58.083
<i>A one-track path that's…</i>

574
00:33:58.166 --> 00:33:59.000
Your turn.

575
00:34:02.416 --> 00:34:04.166
Come on.

576
00:34:05.500 --> 00:34:07.208
Down. Down.

577
00:34:07.291 --> 00:34:08.291
It's not working.

578
00:34:08.375 --> 00:34:10.000
Would you like a snack. Gaga?

579
00:34:10.083 --> 00:34:12.875
<i>I feel it coming for me</i>
<i>Payback. payback</i>

580
00:34:17.458 --> 00:34:19.750
<i>Doo-doo-doo-doo-doo-doo-doo…</i>

581
00:34:28.958 --> 00:34:30.833
Helmut. calm her. Be the leader.

582
00:34:37.375 --> 00:34:39.166
I see room for improvement.

583
00:34:39.250 --> 00:34:41.500
Your next task is all about trust.

584
00:34:46.541 --> 00:34:51.791
Okay. please take off the leashes
and bring your dogs into the water.

585
00:34:51.875 --> 00:34:53.000
Um…

586
00:34:54.250 --> 00:34:55.208
- Helmut.
- Hmm?

587
00:34:55.291 --> 00:34:57.166
You can leave the leash on. all right?

588
00:34:57.916 --> 00:34:59.833
The current is a bit too strong for Gaga.

589
00:35:00.541 --> 00:35:03.916
Helmi. just carry Gaga in your arms.
The water is way too strong.

590
00:35:04.000 --> 00:35:05.750
Gaga almost drowned in the bathtub.

591
00:35:07.833 --> 00:35:09.166
You think Gaga can make it happen?

592
00:35:13.041 --> 00:35:15.458
Uh. I don't know for sure.

593
00:35:15.541 --> 00:35:17.041
I don't want anything to happen to her.

594
00:35:17.125 --> 00:35:18.875
And I'm not very happy with this either.

595
00:35:18.958 --> 00:35:21.333
Hey. man.
you gotta stop getting so wound up.

596
00:35:21.416 --> 00:35:24.166
All right. Ziggy. that's enough.
Gaga's ready to go.

597
00:35:24.916 --> 00:35:26.208
It'll be fine.

598
00:35:26.291 --> 00:35:28.750
Gaga's my little princess.
don't you forget.

599
00:35:29.250 --> 00:35:31.541
Well. I hope she's not
the only one to you.

600
00:35:32.291 --> 00:35:34.750
Let's go. Gaga.
it's our turn in the spotlight.

601
00:35:34.833 --> 00:35:36.291
Oh…

602
00:35:43.625 --> 00:35:47.416
Good. Helmut.
See what happens when you work together?

603
00:35:50.083 --> 00:35:53.291
Okay. so I'm gonna go over there.
and you can do whatever you want.

604
00:36:01.416 --> 00:36:02.791
That's great. Urschi.

605
00:36:05.458 --> 00:36:07.000
- You're next. Babs.
- Okay.

606
00:36:08.083 --> 00:36:10.666
We're next. Torsten. We can do this.

607
00:36:14.250 --> 00:36:16.250
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

608
00:36:18.041 --> 00:36:19.708
Torsten. please come.

609
00:36:19.791 --> 00:36:20.708
Torsten!

610
00:36:20.791 --> 00:36:22.375
No. no. no. no. not like that!

611
00:36:22.458 --> 00:36:24.333
Oh please. Torsten.

612
00:36:27.333 --> 00:36:28.625
Ahh!

613
00:36:31.291 --> 00:36:32.833
Shit.

614
00:36:33.583 --> 00:36:34.958
Urschi!

615
00:36:35.041 --> 00:36:36.791
I'm so sorry. are you okay?

616
00:36:38.916 --> 00:36:40.291
It's my fault.

617
00:36:44.000 --> 00:36:45.250
You know what I learned?

618
00:36:46.625 --> 00:36:48.333
I thought it was the dog.

619
00:36:48.416 --> 00:36:51.416
But now I realize. Torsten's not at fault.

620
00:36:52.000 --> 00:36:53.875
You're the one to blame!

621
00:37:03.791 --> 00:37:04.625
Babs…

622
00:37:04.708 --> 00:37:06.375
Hey.

623
00:37:07.541 --> 00:37:08.458
It's okay.

624
00:37:14.208 --> 00:37:16.625
What's happening with Roxy?

625
00:37:16.708 --> 00:37:19.958
She's just a coward. man.
She won't go near the water.

626
00:37:25.833 --> 00:37:27.333
You're not the problem. Roxy.

627
00:37:27.416 --> 00:37:29.750
The problem's on
the other end of your leash.

628
00:37:32.916 --> 00:37:34.791
If you want Roxy's trust.

629
00:37:36.000 --> 00:37:37.958
you will have to prove that you trust her.

630
00:37:52.500 --> 00:37:53.750
Here you are.

631
00:37:56.958 --> 00:37:58.916
Mm…

632
00:37:59.000 --> 00:38:00.416
Is this a magic potion?

633
00:38:00.500 --> 00:38:01.500
No. it's just soup.

634
00:38:01.583 --> 00:38:02.750
Magical soup?

635
00:38:04.333 --> 00:38:05.958
It's a Celtic soup.

636
00:38:10.083 --> 00:38:12.583
This is a magical soup.

637
00:38:12.666 --> 00:38:14.958
It's yesterday's leftovers.
just covered in water.

638
00:38:21.791 --> 00:38:23.791
Mm…

639
00:38:23.875 --> 00:38:26.833
Mm…

640
00:38:27.375 --> 00:38:31.708
Nature. we thank you here

641
00:38:31.791 --> 00:38:38.625
that you have so generously
provided us today.

642
00:38:38.708 --> 00:38:40.666
We honor you.

643
00:38:40.750 --> 00:38:43.083
respect you.

644
00:38:43.166 --> 00:38:48.083
and protect you.

645
00:38:48.166 --> 00:38:51.125
Thank you for this magical soup.

646
00:38:51.208 --> 00:38:52.625
Enjoy your meal.

647
00:39:19.041 --> 00:39:21.458
Ugh. That is so disgusting.

648
00:39:22.625 --> 00:39:26.666
Urschi. Urschi. I'm starting to get
the feeling that you don't like Brenda.

649
00:39:26.750 --> 00:39:29.833
This has nothing to do with Brenda.
I hate all dogs.

650
00:39:30.458 --> 00:39:31.583
What?

651
00:39:32.083 --> 00:39:34.041
I knew you didn't know
anything about dogs.

652
00:39:34.125 --> 00:39:36.375
but this is basically a hate crime.

653
00:39:37.708 --> 00:39:39.750
Brenda is not my dog.

654
00:39:44.583 --> 00:39:45.833
Wait a minute.

655
00:39:45.916 --> 00:39:46.916
Ugh…

656
00:39:47.000 --> 00:39:48.291
Okay. here's my story.

657
00:39:49.375 --> 00:39:50.541
It's hard to believe.

658
00:39:51.833 --> 00:39:57.250
I have a very dear friend. and she's
severely disabled and so very lonely.

659
00:39:57.333 --> 00:39:59.750
And we formed our friend group
for her sake

660
00:39:59.833 --> 00:40:01.416
so she wouldn't be so sad and alone.

661
00:40:02.041 --> 00:40:05.375
So. of course we quickly found out
Brenda is possessed by the devil.

662
00:40:06.416 --> 00:40:10.916
And yeah. I promised my friend
I'd take Brenda up here to Nodon.

663
00:40:13.083 --> 00:40:16.333
Sometimes you must make sacrifices
on behalf of a friend.

664
00:40:16.416 --> 00:40:19.250
and that is why I am such a good person.

665
00:40:21.208 --> 00:40:24.791
I think that's… That is so amazing.

666
00:40:25.666 --> 00:40:26.583
Thank you. Babs.

667
00:40:26.666 --> 00:40:29.250
You'd do the same
for your friends as well.

668
00:40:29.333 --> 00:40:30.458
Definitely. yes.

669
00:40:33.458 --> 00:40:35.708
Okay. Let's return to our training.

670
00:40:35.791 --> 00:40:39.250
Um. Nodon.
Babs has another question for you. hm?

671
00:40:39.333 --> 00:40:41.833
Ah. it's okay.

672
00:40:41.916 --> 00:40:43.083
What is it?

673
00:40:43.166 --> 00:40:45.250
Mm… Okay. Um…

674
00:40:46.125 --> 00:40:48.083
Ah so. uh… so tonight
there is some entertainment.

675
00:40:48.166 --> 00:40:50.375
Like Tyrolean music and other fun stuff.

676
00:40:51.000 --> 00:40:53.541
Oh yeah. and you can
bring your dogs as well.

677
00:40:53.625 --> 00:40:56.375
It's a great chance for them
to experience stressful situations.

678
00:40:56.458 --> 00:40:59.708
That's not what I meant. Um. will you. uh…

679
00:40:59.791 --> 00:41:03.000
Uh. so we. uh. all wanted to ask. um. uh…

680
00:41:03.625 --> 00:41:04.791
You planning on going?

681
00:41:04.875 --> 00:41:06.375
No. Babs.

682
00:41:06.458 --> 00:41:07.875
The entertainment is for the guests.

683
00:41:08.833 --> 00:41:11.416
My world is peace. and nature. in harmony.

684
00:41:13.000 --> 00:41:14.916
- So. Hakan.
- Yeah?

685
00:41:15.000 --> 00:41:17.791
Will you be joining your group
at this evening's festivities?

686
00:41:17.875 --> 00:41:18.875
It's not my thing.

687
00:41:19.875 --> 00:41:20.916
It's not optional.

688
00:41:22.125 --> 00:41:25.708
I promised my wife I'd come here.
But yodeling wasn't part of the deal.

689
00:41:27.833 --> 00:41:29.166
It's all part of the training.

690
00:41:31.625 --> 00:41:35.000
Come here. sweetie. Good.

691
00:41:36.000 --> 00:41:39.041
And for the rest of the day.
Helmut. you're in charge of Gaga.

692
00:41:39.125 --> 00:41:40.583
Yeah. yeah. yeah. Yeah. yeah.

693
00:42:15.541 --> 00:42:17.708
Hmm. Mm.

694
00:42:27.208 --> 00:42:30.750
[intriguing music playing

695
00:42:42.916 --> 00:42:44.916
BAVARIAN STATE MINISTER

696
00:42:49.041 --> 00:42:51.291
{\an8}SCANDALOUS VIDEO

697
00:43:08.000 --> 00:43:09.583
RECEPTION

698
00:43:27.125 --> 00:43:29.375
<i>- Do you own a dog?</i>
- <i>Oh God. no.</i>

699
00:43:29.458 --> 00:43:33.041
<i>I'd much rather poke out my eyes</i>
<i>than have one of those brutes in my house.</i>

700
00:43:33.125 --> 00:43:36.375
<i>But for many people. their dog is</i>
<i>their most significant life partner.</i>

701
00:43:36.458 --> 00:43:41.416
<i>Wow. if my pet was my significant</i>
<i>life partner. you might as well kill me.</i>

702
00:43:41.500 --> 00:43:43.375
<i>We had a problem with the clip.</i>

703
00:43:43.458 --> 00:43:46.000
Really? I've only been gone for 36 hours!

704
00:43:50.000 --> 00:43:52.625
No. I don't think
I'm hearing you correctly.

705
00:43:52.708 --> 00:43:54.958
Say it again but be more clear.

706
00:43:55.041 --> 00:43:57.416
<i>I don't think</i>
<i>I could be any clearer. Ursula.</i>

707
00:43:57.500 --> 00:44:00.000
Anything else I should know?
Something you're not telling me?

708
00:44:00.083 --> 00:44:03.333
<i>They're getting cold feet. They are</i>
<i>auditioning replacement candidates.</i>

709
00:44:03.416 --> 00:44:05.166
What? Well. who?

710
00:44:05.250 --> 00:44:06.708
<i>Martin Weidenhuber.</i>

711
00:44:07.250 --> 00:44:10.666
Have they gone crazy?
He embezzled public funds and got a DUI.

712
00:44:10.750 --> 00:44:11.666
<i>So what?</i>

713
00:44:11.750 --> 00:44:15.041
<i>He went to rehab. got his license back.</i>
<i>and apologized for the embezzling.</i>

714
00:44:15.125 --> 00:44:17.166
Yeah. but this is absurd.

715
00:44:17.250 --> 00:44:19.500
He keeps bouncing back
after every stupid thing he does.

716
00:44:19.583 --> 00:44:21.875
but I'm the one who's out
because I don't like dogs?

717
00:44:21.958 --> 00:44:23.916
<i>No one said it's fair.</i>

718
00:44:24.000 --> 00:44:28.000
<i>Life is always stacked against women.</i>
<i>especially in politics.</i>

719
00:44:28.083 --> 00:44:30.041
<i>But you knew that getting in the game.</i>

720
00:44:31.583 --> 00:44:32.791
I know.

721
00:44:34.750 --> 00:44:38.250
<i>Let's stick to the plan.</i>
<i>You'll appear on </i>Live on Wednesday.

722
00:44:38.333 --> 00:44:39.166
Yeah. good.

723
00:44:49.333 --> 00:44:51.125
What are you doing in my office?

724
00:44:51.208 --> 00:44:52.166
Well. um…

725
00:44:52.250 --> 00:44:54.375
Any particular reason for being here?

726
00:44:55.708 --> 00:44:56.541
Who are you?

727
00:44:56.625 --> 00:44:58.625
Simon Reisinger.

728
00:44:58.708 --> 00:45:00.250
I am the innkeeper and owner.

729
00:45:00.333 --> 00:45:02.833
Ah. this makes sense now.

730
00:45:02.916 --> 00:45:05.666
All of our phones were taken away
by your elderly forest gnome.

731
00:45:05.750 --> 00:45:06.916
That is not all right.

732
00:45:07.000 --> 00:45:09.875
Not my issue.
because when Nodon has a group here.

733
00:45:10.583 --> 00:45:12.000
he makes the rules.

734
00:45:12.083 --> 00:45:13.458
It's out of my hands.

735
00:45:13.541 --> 00:45:16.000
- That's not a good answer.
- Well. it's all I've got.

736
00:45:16.083 --> 00:45:17.500
And you can leave. please.

737
00:45:18.583 --> 00:45:20.416
You'll be hearing from my attorney.

738
00:45:20.500 --> 00:45:22.458
I cannot recommend your establishment.

739
00:45:23.375 --> 00:45:24.291
Fine.

740
00:45:24.875 --> 00:45:27.750
In that case.
I can't recommend you as a guest as well.

741
00:45:27.833 --> 00:45:31.250
Torsten. isn't this music so beautiful?

742
00:45:31.333 --> 00:45:33.875
Torsten. come. Now. please.

743
00:45:34.708 --> 00:45:36.041
Torsten. now. please.

744
00:45:36.666 --> 00:45:38.291
Good.

745
00:45:38.375 --> 00:45:40.583
Now. just like your little friend Gaga.

746
00:45:42.416 --> 00:45:43.375
Helmut?

747
00:45:43.458 --> 00:45:44.750
Gaga is gone.

748
00:45:45.875 --> 00:45:46.958
Ziggy!

749
00:45:48.791 --> 00:45:50.958
Yeah. so that's how you care for our baby.

750
00:45:51.041 --> 00:45:52.291
Anyone could have stolen her.

751
00:45:52.375 --> 00:45:54.458
Let that be a lesson.
Gaga doesn't belong on the floor.

752
00:45:54.541 --> 00:45:57.000
That is the dumbest thing
you've said to me.

753
00:45:57.083 --> 00:45:58.875
Have you been sniffing
your Sea Breeze candles?

754
00:45:58.958 --> 00:46:01.416
You're just acting like you're worked up.
part of your plan.

755
00:46:01.500 --> 00:46:02.791
Wh… what goddamn plan?

756
00:46:02.875 --> 00:46:05.000
You're trying to make
my Gaga love you more!

757
00:46:05.083 --> 00:46:07.041
All I want is for her to stop biting me.

758
00:46:07.125 --> 00:46:09.625
- Why we're here. in case you forgot.
- Enough. please!

759
00:46:09.708 --> 00:46:12.166
Just stop screaming. I can't…

760
00:46:18.666 --> 00:46:19.541
You are unbelievable!

761
00:46:19.625 --> 00:46:22.500
Don't you realize you're in
the presence of a musical genius?

762
00:46:24.166 --> 00:46:25.375
Ahh!

763
00:46:26.625 --> 00:46:28.000
Oh my Lord in heaven.

764
00:46:28.083 --> 00:46:30.666
You're incapable of
keeping control of your dog.

765
00:46:30.750 --> 00:46:32.750
It's shameful to humans everywhere.

766
00:46:32.833 --> 00:46:35.500
And now you're crying too. Stupid.

767
00:46:35.583 --> 00:46:37.291
Hey. look after her.

768
00:46:37.375 --> 00:46:39.541
What a mess!

769
00:46:42.250 --> 00:46:44.291
Sorry. Babs.
but I have to take the dog out.

770
00:46:47.083 --> 00:46:48.250
Oy.

771
00:46:51.500 --> 00:46:53.958
Have you gone
completely mental around here?

772
00:46:54.041 --> 00:46:57.375
I'm leaving! Hey. Gustl.
take me to the village immediately.

773
00:46:58.416 --> 00:47:01.708
Our Gustl won't drive anyone tonight.

774
00:47:01.791 --> 00:47:03.833
No one gets an early departure.

775
00:47:07.083 --> 00:47:08.500
What's going on?

776
00:47:11.500 --> 00:47:12.958
They will take him away.

777
00:47:13.041 --> 00:47:16.916
This was our last chance.
and we blew it completely.

778
00:47:17.000 --> 00:47:19.541
Now. now. all is good. come on over here.

779
00:47:20.041 --> 00:47:22.375
We did everything wrong.

780
00:47:22.458 --> 00:47:25.750
Come on. Ziggy. you're jealous because
Gaga and I made it happen today.

781
00:47:25.833 --> 00:47:27.541
Ow! Ach!

782
00:47:27.625 --> 00:47:29.208
It serves you right.

783
00:47:33.458 --> 00:47:35.958
Okay. okay. let's calm down.

784
00:47:40.375 --> 00:47:43.208
What do you mean. they'll take him
away from you? Who are "they"?

785
00:47:43.291 --> 00:47:45.458
The damn veterinarian. I mean.

786
00:47:45.541 --> 00:47:47.875
If I can't prove
I have control over Torsten's behavior.

787
00:47:47.958 --> 00:47:49.708
they won't let him stay with me.

788
00:47:50.375 --> 00:47:51.416
Just tell them you do.

789
00:47:51.500 --> 00:47:53.000
They check up on it.

790
00:47:53.083 --> 00:47:55.833
Torsten needs to pass a temperament test.

791
00:47:55.916 --> 00:47:59.333
And me. the dog handler's test.

792
00:47:59.416 --> 00:48:01.625
He's considered a danger to the public.

793
00:48:03.875 --> 00:48:05.916
That does seem to be a problem.

794
00:48:08.250 --> 00:48:12.458
It's time for you to talk differently
to your friend Torsten. okay. Babs?

795
00:48:13.708 --> 00:48:15.458
You be the boss.

796
00:48:16.583 --> 00:48:18.250
Make the boundaries clear to him.

797
00:48:18.333 --> 00:48:22.250
Yeah. but what if
he refuses to like me anymore?

798
00:48:25.708 --> 00:48:29.375
Look. Simon. this can't continue.

799
00:48:29.875 --> 00:48:32.958
These hooligans are rioting.
smashing up my furniture.

800
00:48:33.041 --> 00:48:35.000
and destroying everything.
Please send them home.

801
00:48:35.083 --> 00:48:37.416
I can't do that to their dogs.

802
00:48:37.500 --> 00:48:39.458
They haven't done anything wrong.

803
00:48:39.541 --> 00:48:40.666
The people are the problem.

804
00:48:40.750 --> 00:48:42.958
Yeah. that much is clear.

805
00:48:43.041 --> 00:48:45.166
But some of them are way beyond help.

806
00:48:45.250 --> 00:48:46.458
Especially overnight.

807
00:48:46.541 --> 00:48:48.166
Look. you only have tomorrow left.

808
00:48:48.250 --> 00:48:49.333
I know.

809
00:48:50.083 --> 00:48:51.666
That's why I must come up with something.

810
00:48:51.750 --> 00:48:54.791
Something that inspires them
and wakes them up.

811
00:48:54.875 --> 00:48:55.958
Mm.

812
00:49:03.083 --> 00:49:04.208
What is that?

813
00:49:04.750 --> 00:49:06.666
It's a mood stabilizer.

814
00:49:07.708 --> 00:49:09.791
I'd love one of those today. Every day.

815
00:49:10.791 --> 00:49:12.250
- Mm?
- Mm.

816
00:49:12.875 --> 00:49:13.916
No. thanks.

817
00:49:14.875 --> 00:49:18.666
You know. I was. um.
in a clinic for a while.

818
00:49:18.750 --> 00:49:22.125
because of mental problems. as they say.

819
00:49:22.208 --> 00:49:24.250
I'm still dealing with that.

820
00:49:24.833 --> 00:49:27.791
And those doctors have provided me
with tools to help cope and improve life.

821
00:49:27.875 --> 00:49:31.875
One of those was to get a dog. When you
cuddle dogs. it does something in you.

822
00:49:31.958 --> 00:49:33.833
It releases hormones.

823
00:49:33.916 --> 00:49:37.000
It's good for the body and the mind.
and many things.

824
00:49:37.583 --> 00:49:41.416
Torsten is not only a great dog.
but he's the most important person to me.

825
00:49:41.500 --> 00:49:42.583
Dog.

826
00:49:43.916 --> 00:49:45.208
Torsten is a dog.

827
00:49:46.916 --> 00:49:47.916
Yeah.

828
00:49:49.083 --> 00:49:51.083
But for me. he's better than any person.

829
00:49:56.166 --> 00:49:58.416
So you're saying he's your most important

830
00:49:59.500 --> 00:50:00.500
social partner?

831
00:50:01.666 --> 00:50:03.416
That's it!

832
00:50:04.416 --> 00:50:05.708
You got that right.

833
00:50:50.500 --> 00:50:52.333
You're like a child.

834
00:50:52.416 --> 00:50:54.625
Gaga and I need alone time.
You are not invited!

835
00:50:54.708 --> 00:50:57.000
- Stop being a drama queen!
- Hey!

836
00:50:58.500 --> 00:51:00.375
- Oh. um…
- What did you say to me?

837
00:51:00.458 --> 00:51:03.041
- Sorry. uh. were we too loud?
- What's all this?

838
00:51:03.916 --> 00:51:06.833
Well. uh… My husband. he…

839
00:51:07.666 --> 00:51:10.916
- …locked me out. I can't get in.
- Yeah. and?

840
00:51:11.000 --> 00:51:14.416
Yeah. well. um. it's kind of stupid.

841
00:51:14.500 --> 00:51:16.875
I don't really have another place to go.

842
00:51:16.958 --> 00:51:18.416
Yeah.

843
00:51:19.875 --> 00:51:21.958
Well. come in. I have a couch.

844
00:51:22.041 --> 00:51:23.916
Yeah. well. uh… Mm…

845
00:51:24.000 --> 00:51:26.125
That's a very nice offer.

846
00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:30.875
But I… I can't accept. It's very kind.
but it wouldn't… Thank you. but no.

847
00:51:30.958 --> 00:51:33.500
- You scared of me?
- Scared? Me?

848
00:51:34.541 --> 00:51:36.416
No. Why? What…

849
00:51:37.125 --> 00:51:38.125
That's strange.

850
00:51:40.416 --> 00:51:42.375
Most are afraid of me.

851
00:51:43.083 --> 00:51:44.666
Even the hardened ones.

852
00:51:45.458 --> 00:51:48.791
Drugs. robbery. human trafficking.

853
00:51:52.041 --> 00:51:54.750
Hey. hey. come on.

854
00:51:54.833 --> 00:51:56.125
Kidding! I'm a police officer.

855
00:51:57.250 --> 00:51:58.166
A police officer?

856
00:51:58.958 --> 00:51:59.958
Yeah.

857
00:52:04.625 --> 00:52:06.333
Ah… I guess you are.

858
00:52:07.041 --> 00:52:10.125
That's. um… That's so weird.
Crazy. I never would have guessed.

859
00:52:11.333 --> 00:52:12.333
Yeah.

860
00:52:12.416 --> 00:52:15.458
I thought…
That makes Roxy a police dog. right?

861
00:52:15.541 --> 00:52:17.583
She's retired. so…

862
00:52:17.666 --> 00:52:19.291
What? She looks way too young.

863
00:52:19.916 --> 00:52:20.833
Really.

864
00:52:20.916 --> 00:52:23.500
- We should bandage that up. Come on.
- Yes. we should.

865
00:52:24.083 --> 00:52:27.958
A police officer and his dog
should serve and protect.

866
00:52:28.041 --> 00:52:30.125
I really didn't expect this at all.

867
00:52:36.916 --> 00:52:39.750
I can't wait to see
what Legolas has planned for us today.

868
00:52:39.833 --> 00:52:41.416
That's not his name.

869
00:52:41.500 --> 00:52:44.666
Oh. by the way. are you feeling anything
from his magic potion yet?

870
00:52:44.750 --> 00:52:47.208
A bit. don't you think?

871
00:52:47.291 --> 00:52:49.208
Babs. Babs. you're mental.

872
00:52:49.291 --> 00:52:51.875
Looks like you're in a good mood.
What. did someone die?

873
00:52:51.958 --> 00:52:53.500
Hmm…

874
00:52:54.166 --> 00:52:56.833
That's fair. I deserve that remark.

875
00:52:58.500 --> 00:53:00.083
So. did you sleep well?

876
00:53:00.708 --> 00:53:02.291
Troubles in paradise?

877
00:53:02.875 --> 00:53:04.875
Yeah. we're having a fight. That's it.

878
00:53:04.958 --> 00:53:06.916
You fought? No way.

879
00:53:07.541 --> 00:53:11.708
So. ungrateful guests.
Gustl awaits you in his wagon.

880
00:53:11.791 --> 00:53:14.166
And behave yourselves this time. okay?

881
00:53:14.250 --> 00:53:16.541
Where are we off to this time?
Nodon's hut?

882
00:53:16.625 --> 00:53:18.458
Wait and see. What do I know?

883
00:53:22.041 --> 00:53:23.041
Come.

884
00:53:28.708 --> 00:53:31.458
That breakfast will come up
with just one more shake.

885
00:53:32.041 --> 00:53:33.791
I'm glad I didn't eat.

886
00:53:34.833 --> 00:53:36.750
Ya! Ya!

887
00:53:37.625 --> 00:53:40.458
They're coming. Heidi.
It's our last chance.

888
00:53:52.375 --> 00:53:54.166
He wears less clothing every day.

889
00:53:54.250 --> 00:53:56.583
- If it lasted any longer. he'd be naked.
- Yeah.

890
00:53:56.666 --> 00:53:58.916
- I don't mind staying an extra day.
- Oh. Ziggy.

891
00:53:59.000 --> 00:53:59.833
Welcome!

892
00:54:00.416 --> 00:54:04.000
You have arrived
at a very sacred place. dear dagdas.

893
00:54:05.833 --> 00:54:07.750
This is the tent of truth.

894
00:54:08.875 --> 00:54:12.208
Many rituals and ceremonies
have taken place here.

895
00:54:12.708 --> 00:54:15.083
The effects of them can still be felt.

896
00:54:16.791 --> 00:54:18.208
Babs.

897
00:54:18.291 --> 00:54:19.291
You're first.

898
00:54:24.750 --> 00:54:26.833
May you feel power in this place.

899
00:54:28.083 --> 00:54:29.708
Let the Tree of Life…

900
00:54:33.041 --> 00:54:34.083
and its wisdom…

901
00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:37.208
be with you.

902
00:54:41.083 --> 00:54:42.250
Please go in.

903
00:54:52.333 --> 00:54:56.125
<i>Kumaber nichte enteitesoo.</i>

904
00:54:57.291 --> 00:55:01.666
<i>Teiseles shonata oine sinapaa.</i>

905
00:55:02.416 --> 00:55:05.541
<i>Faumaderkuu iteakaa.</i>

906
00:55:05.625 --> 00:55:08.958
I really hope
his insurance covers ceremonies.

907
00:55:09.041 --> 00:55:13.416
Your dogs… are the mirror of your soul.

908
00:55:14.000 --> 00:55:16.583
They feel all that worries you.
that upsets you.

909
00:55:16.666 --> 00:55:18.000
bothers you.

910
00:55:18.583 --> 00:55:20.250
and reflect it back.

911
00:55:21.541 --> 00:55:25.125
The most important step
is to recognize this.

912
00:55:25.791 --> 00:55:28.208
and work on making big changes.

913
00:55:31.541 --> 00:55:33.291
You all have a chance.

914
00:55:34.291 --> 00:55:36.750
For you. But above all.

915
00:55:37.958 --> 00:55:39.333
for your dogs.

916
00:55:50.250 --> 00:55:51.250
Babs.

917
00:55:52.250 --> 00:55:53.916
Tell me what happened last night.

918
00:55:55.000 --> 00:55:58.291
How did you react when you witnessed
Ziggy and Helmut fighting?

919
00:56:00.750 --> 00:56:06.041
It's very difficult for me when…
people are fighting around me.

920
00:56:06.125 --> 00:56:07.583
And Torsten?

921
00:56:09.041 --> 00:56:10.541
He was nervous.

922
00:56:10.625 --> 00:56:11.875
Do you see what's happening?

923
00:56:14.500 --> 00:56:16.458
This is my fault.

924
00:56:17.750 --> 00:56:19.291
It's my fault.

925
00:56:20.583 --> 00:56:22.791
I messed everything up.

926
00:56:32.166 --> 00:56:34.291
If you embrace
your strength and tranquility.

927
00:56:35.291 --> 00:56:36.541
you'll see Torsten relax.

928
00:56:38.583 --> 00:56:41.000
Babs. what's bothering you?

929
00:56:41.666 --> 00:56:43.375
What causes you angst?

930
00:56:43.458 --> 00:56:46.625
I have this fear
of saying the wrong thing.

931
00:56:46.708 --> 00:56:48.958
and that people will stop
associating with me.

932
00:56:50.666 --> 00:56:52.791
See. most people don't like me.

933
00:56:53.291 --> 00:56:54.500
And I'm not sure why.

934
00:56:54.583 --> 00:56:56.458
But it's different with Torsten.

935
00:56:56.958 --> 00:56:58.958
He's always sweet and kind to me.

936
00:56:59.041 --> 00:57:01.250
He seems to like me for me.

937
00:57:01.750 --> 00:57:04.916
He doesn't mind if I'm taking medication.
and he never judges me.

938
00:57:05.458 --> 00:57:07.750
The only one in my life
who has never judged me.

939
00:57:08.750 --> 00:57:10.375
Babs. we're not judging you.

940
00:57:11.250 --> 00:57:12.416
You're doing great.

941
00:57:12.500 --> 00:57:14.791
Finding medicine that helps
is a great step.

942
00:57:15.666 --> 00:57:16.666
Right?

943
00:57:16.750 --> 00:57:18.625
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah. it's not a big deal.

944
00:57:18.708 --> 00:57:20.833
My doctor prescribed me antidepressants.

945
00:57:23.791 --> 00:57:24.791
Really?

946
00:57:26.541 --> 00:57:28.958
- Babs. you have a goal.
- Yeah.

947
00:57:29.041 --> 00:57:32.750
Torsten needs to obey your commands
all the time. That's why you're here.

948
00:57:32.833 --> 00:57:36.875
Show him your ability to lead
with clear. short commands.

949
00:57:38.000 --> 00:57:39.583
He'll be grateful.

950
00:57:40.791 --> 00:57:41.708
That's what he needs.

951
00:57:42.833 --> 00:57:45.750
Ah. well. it seems to me
that if it's that easy…

952
00:57:45.833 --> 00:57:47.541
…why doesn't Brenda
follow a single command?

953
00:57:47.625 --> 00:57:50.750
I mean.
leadership skills is what I'm known for.

954
00:57:51.916 --> 00:57:54.375
- Is that because of your work?
- Yeah.

955
00:57:54.958 --> 00:57:56.083
No.

956
00:57:56.708 --> 00:57:59.375
So. what's going on. then.
between Brenda and me?

957
00:58:00.625 --> 00:58:02.875
So Brenda must know
where she stands with you.

958
00:58:03.500 --> 00:58:04.375
You both are a team.

959
00:58:06.416 --> 00:58:07.458
Isn't that right?

960
00:58:08.083 --> 00:58:10.791
Yeah. but don't forget.
Brenda isn't even her dog.

961
00:58:10.875 --> 00:58:12.958
- Brenda's just a loaner.
- That's true.

962
00:58:13.041 --> 00:58:16.333
And not only that.
she told us that she's not a dog person.

963
00:58:16.416 --> 00:58:18.666
Oh. but you're big fan of dogs now?

964
00:58:19.750 --> 00:58:24.500
Yeah. but that's only because
I was able to bond with Gaga yesterday.

965
00:58:24.583 --> 00:58:27.041
Probably because you didn't intervene.
for once.

966
00:58:27.125 --> 00:58:29.000
Is that true. Ziggy?

967
00:58:29.083 --> 00:58:33.250
Are you subconsciously sabotaging
Helmut and Gaga because you're jealous?

968
00:58:34.375 --> 00:58:36.208
- Me?
- Yeah.

969
00:58:36.291 --> 00:58:37.500
I'm the saboteur?

970
00:58:38.625 --> 00:58:40.416
Ugh. it's the other way around.

971
00:58:40.500 --> 00:58:44.666
Yeah. Ask him about how he reprimands me
anytime I buy Gaga something nice to wear.

972
00:58:44.750 --> 00:58:46.833
Doggie couture doesn't pay for itself.

973
00:58:46.916 --> 00:58:48.625
This is why I'm starting
my candle business.

974
00:58:48.708 --> 00:58:50.375
Right. Caribbean.

975
00:58:50.458 --> 00:58:53.500
You see that? See how he makes fun of me?

976
00:58:53.583 --> 00:58:57.583
Oh please… I'm on your side. I'm thrilled
you're starting your own company.

977
00:58:57.666 --> 00:59:00.541
Oh. right.
Sabine told me exactly how you operate.

978
00:59:00.625 --> 00:59:01.625
- Oh. Sabine?
- Yeah.

979
00:59:01.708 --> 00:59:03.958
Yeah. You frequently complain
when I spend your money.

980
00:59:04.041 --> 00:59:06.541
but secretly.
you want me dependent on you. Helmut.

981
00:59:06.625 --> 00:59:08.166
so you can control everything!

982
00:59:08.250 --> 00:59:10.791
Oh please. not this again.

983
00:59:10.875 --> 00:59:13.375
Are we talking about the same Sabine
who says I'm on the spectrum?

984
00:59:13.458 --> 00:59:17.375
Did you discover this "therapist"
on the ad board at the supermarket?

985
00:59:17.458 --> 00:59:19.291
Why don't you two just break up?

986
00:59:22.458 --> 00:59:23.583
Uh. pardon?

987
00:59:27.583 --> 00:59:29.250
Maybe Hakan's right.

988
00:59:29.333 --> 00:59:31.791
You've been fighting since you got here.

989
00:59:31.875 --> 00:59:32.875
And your poor dog

990
00:59:34.333 --> 00:59:35.833
is the victim of your egos.

991
00:59:38.500 --> 00:59:41.375
Yeah. so I thought that
we had come here for dog training.

992
00:59:41.458 --> 00:59:43.416
Yeah! Exactly.

993
00:59:43.500 --> 00:59:45.750
Instead he's just
breaking up our relationship.

994
00:59:45.833 --> 00:59:48.375
- Oh. sorry. but--
- I'm done listening to this nonsense.

995
00:59:48.458 --> 00:59:50.041
Amateur psychology.

996
00:59:50.125 --> 00:59:51.791
Come. Ziggy. we're going. Come.

997
00:59:51.875 --> 00:59:53.375
Coming. my love.

998
00:59:54.708 --> 00:59:57.833
Well. then. um. I'm leaving too.

999
00:59:58.541 --> 00:59:59.541
Come.

1000
01:00:03.291 --> 01:00:04.333
Help him.

1001
01:00:04.916 --> 01:00:06.750
Torsten. sit.

1002
01:00:11.125 --> 01:00:12.041
It worked.

1003
01:00:17.958 --> 01:00:19.541
Hakan. why are you mad at Roxy?

1004
01:00:20.916 --> 01:00:22.250
Did she bite someone?

1005
01:00:24.291 --> 01:00:25.791
She's not a biter.

1006
01:00:25.875 --> 01:00:28.708
She wears a muzzle
even though she's not bitten anyone?

1007
01:00:32.833 --> 01:00:35.458
Is this a form of punishment?

1008
01:00:36.250 --> 01:00:38.083
It's her fault my brother is dead.

1009
01:00:43.458 --> 01:00:48.000
Um. I. um… I need a break.

1010
01:00:50.708 --> 01:00:51.791
Come. Torsten.

1011
01:00:58.666 --> 01:01:00.000
What happened?

1012
01:01:01.375 --> 01:01:02.791
What did Roxy do?

1013
01:01:07.875 --> 01:01:11.125
It's a total disgrace what this crackpot
Celt is doing with all of us.

1014
01:01:11.208 --> 01:01:13.041
It's nuts.
What kind of madman talks like that?

1015
01:01:13.125 --> 01:01:16.416
I was suspicious of the whole Celtic
hocus-pocus from the beginning.

1016
01:01:16.500 --> 01:01:17.958
I'm ready to leave. You?

1017
01:01:18.041 --> 01:01:19.250
- Yeah. me too.
- Good.

1018
01:01:20.250 --> 01:01:23.333
Come. Ziggy.
Gustl can return for the others later.

1019
01:01:23.833 --> 01:01:25.541
You are absolutely right. my dear.

1020
01:01:27.541 --> 01:01:29.541
How about you? Coming with us?

1021
01:01:29.625 --> 01:01:31.416
Uh. I'm gonna stick around
for a little while.

1022
01:01:31.500 --> 01:01:33.583
I want to practice some more with Torsten.

1023
01:01:34.083 --> 01:01:35.291
Do what you want.

1024
01:01:36.666 --> 01:01:39.041
That was very brave of you back there.

1025
01:01:58.416 --> 01:02:00.375
Great. It's empty now.

1026
01:02:00.916 --> 01:02:03.583
So. where do you think
they hid our phones? Any idea?

1027
01:02:05.041 --> 01:02:08.250
I couldn't really search yesterday
because I ran into the owner.

1028
01:02:19.708 --> 01:02:22.000
"Will the Reisinger Inn shut down?"

1029
01:02:22.083 --> 01:02:26.500
"Innkeeper Simon Reisinger looks back on
the worst season in their long history."

1030
01:02:26.583 --> 01:02:28.666
"'A miracle is what we need.'
said the young innkeeper.

1031
01:02:28.750 --> 01:02:30.625
'I don't believe we can survive.'"

1032
01:02:30.708 --> 01:02:32.000
My God. he's so handsome!

1033
01:02:32.083 --> 01:02:34.125
Is he?
I only saw him covered in shaving cream.

1034
01:02:34.208 --> 01:02:36.958
Wait a minute.
if you ask me. that's actually…

1035
01:02:38.083 --> 01:02:39.208
- Nodon.
- Nodon.

1036
01:02:49.291 --> 01:02:50.833
Come here. my friends.

1037
01:02:54.833 --> 01:02:56.750
What a cunning bastard!

1038
01:02:56.833 --> 01:03:00.500
He's putting on the mystical Celtic show
to rip us off.

1039
01:03:00.583 --> 01:03:04.375
I don't know… just maybe he's attempting
to save the inn. You think?

1040
01:03:04.458 --> 01:03:06.958
So what? It's still called fraud.

1041
01:03:07.625 --> 01:03:08.958
What do we do now?

1042
01:03:09.041 --> 01:03:11.416
Find our phones. Hm.

1043
01:03:17.583 --> 01:03:19.500
Ugh. so many dead buffalo.

1044
01:03:20.625 --> 01:03:21.541
Look here!

1045
01:03:21.625 --> 01:03:22.916
RELIABLE QUALITY. EVERY SITUATION

1046
01:03:23.708 --> 01:03:25.666
- Oh…
- Celtic toilet paper.

1047
01:03:25.750 --> 01:03:26.833
Oh. Ziggy.

1048
01:03:28.875 --> 01:03:30.291
Ugh.

1049
01:03:33.250 --> 01:03:34.166
Found 'em!

1050
01:03:34.250 --> 01:03:35.500
Oh. thank God.

1051
01:03:37.750 --> 01:03:38.708
Oh…

1052
01:03:38.791 --> 01:03:39.708
Oh…

1053
01:03:40.416 --> 01:03:43.166
So. where exactly did you find
this highly-regarded Celtic dog trainer?

1054
01:03:43.791 --> 01:03:45.083
The guy is a fraud.

1055
01:03:45.166 --> 01:03:46.416
- <i>Listen.</i>
- No. you listen.

1056
01:03:46.500 --> 01:03:48.541
I haven't made any progress
with this damn dog.

1057
01:03:48.625 --> 01:03:50.708
I want you to postpone my TV appearance.

1058
01:03:50.791 --> 01:03:52.000
<i>Ursula. please.</i>

1059
01:03:52.083 --> 01:03:53.333
You can't say "please".

1060
01:03:53.416 --> 01:03:54.791
You're the one who messed up here.

1061
01:03:54.875 --> 01:03:58.125
And just the stress of all this hippie
nature BS is driving me insane!

1062
01:03:58.208 --> 01:03:59.916
- <i>You done?</i>
- Yeah.

1063
01:04:00.000 --> 01:04:01.541
I'm done with this.

1064
01:04:01.625 --> 01:04:02.916
What were you thinking?

1065
01:04:03.541 --> 01:04:06.416
<i>Listen. Ursula. And don't</i>
<i>get mad at me. I'm only the messenger.</i>

1066
01:04:06.500 --> 01:04:09.666
<i>but many people internally</i>
<i>doubt your suitability.</i>

1067
01:04:09.750 --> 01:04:11.000
<i>And so.</i>

1068
01:04:11.833 --> 01:04:16.666
<i>after your epic dog fail on TV.</i>
<i>they'd prefer a more reliable candidate.</i>

1069
01:04:16.750 --> 01:04:20.125
<i>Someone who comes off as dependable.</i>
<i>with people </i>and <i>animals.</i>

1070
01:04:21.416 --> 01:04:22.958
<i>Martin Weidenhuber.</i>

1071
01:04:25.291 --> 01:04:28.500
<i>Ursula? I'm sorry. I really am.</i>

1072
01:04:32.708 --> 01:04:35.250
<i>Hello? Ursula? You still there?</i>

1073
01:04:46.916 --> 01:04:48.541
This Nodon guy. I mean.

1074
01:04:49.375 --> 01:04:50.958
- Simon…
- Simon. yeah.

1075
01:04:51.791 --> 01:04:54.041
He said a lot of meaningless crap.

1076
01:04:54.125 --> 01:04:57.041
What gives him the right to judge us?
He doesn't know us at all.

1077
01:04:57.125 --> 01:04:58.125
Yup.

1078
01:04:59.083 --> 01:05:01.250
Uh… Ziggy?

1079
01:05:01.333 --> 01:05:02.500
Hm?

1080
01:05:05.750 --> 01:05:06.750
I…

1081
01:05:08.541 --> 01:05:10.708
I've been more and more afraid

1082
01:05:11.500 --> 01:05:12.833
that you'll leave me.

1083
01:05:14.958 --> 01:05:16.916
- What makes you think that?
- Well…

1084
01:05:17.500 --> 01:05:19.750
You talk about building
that business on your own.

1085
01:05:21.416 --> 01:05:23.041
That doesn't mean I want to leave you.

1086
01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:25.500
- Hm.
- But I…

1087
01:05:27.375 --> 01:05:29.541
I want to be able to have
some of my own success.

1088
01:05:29.625 --> 01:05:32.125
I don't always want to feel so…

1089
01:05:32.625 --> 01:05:36.708
small and… insignificant when I'm with
the smart and successful professor.

1090
01:05:36.791 --> 01:05:40.375
Yeah. but Ziggy.
you're not small or insignificant.

1091
01:05:40.916 --> 01:05:43.833
You have amazing qualities
I dream of having.

1092
01:05:44.416 --> 01:05:46.916
You're incredibly open
with people everywhere.

1093
01:05:47.000 --> 01:05:49.708
You live in the moment
with passion and joy.

1094
01:05:49.791 --> 01:05:50.791
Hm.

1095
01:05:51.333 --> 01:05:53.625
I hope you know how much you mean to me.

1096
01:05:56.125 --> 01:06:00.791
Maybe I have to show that
more clearly and more often.

1097
01:06:09.083 --> 01:06:10.375
Yes. please.

1098
01:06:12.333 --> 01:06:13.333
It's funny.

1099
01:06:13.958 --> 01:06:16.833
I was beginning to think that Gaga was
the only one that really loved me.

1100
01:06:16.916 --> 01:06:18.625
Oh no.

1101
01:06:19.250 --> 01:06:20.666
No. come on.

1102
01:06:24.583 --> 01:06:25.583
Mm.

1103
01:06:52.125 --> 01:06:53.333
Where's Nodon?

1104
01:06:53.958 --> 01:06:55.416
He went to his hut with Heidi.

1105
01:06:55.500 --> 01:06:57.666
Oh yeah. to his hut now. hmm?

1106
01:06:57.750 --> 01:06:59.583
He's probably frolicking
naked in the grass.

1107
01:06:59.666 --> 01:07:01.416
like all the old Celts used to do.

1108
01:07:01.500 --> 01:07:02.333
Um. what?

1109
01:07:04.875 --> 01:07:06.500
Nodon is a fraud.

1110
01:07:06.583 --> 01:07:08.958
He's not Celtic.
He's just a normal Tyrolean.

1111
01:07:09.041 --> 01:07:11.250
His name's Simon.
and he manages this place.

1112
01:07:12.083 --> 01:07:12.958
Why do you think that?

1113
01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:14.875
We exposed him.

1114
01:07:14.958 --> 01:07:16.916
Mm-hmm. Can you prove it?

1115
01:07:17.000 --> 01:07:18.000
Yeah.

1116
01:07:19.083 --> 01:07:20.166
Come with us.

1117
01:07:21.500 --> 01:07:22.500
No.

1118
01:07:23.750 --> 01:07:24.666
No!

1119
01:07:26.666 --> 01:07:28.875
Nodon is not a fraud. That's unbelievable.

1120
01:07:30.250 --> 01:07:33.458
You don't have to believe us.
Just come in and find out for yourself.

1121
01:07:33.541 --> 01:07:36.416
You know what?
You're making up lies about him.

1122
01:07:36.500 --> 01:07:39.750
It's 'cause you're too stubborn to believe
what he said in that truth tent. isn't it?

1123
01:07:39.833 --> 01:07:42.750
That has almost nothing to do with it.
Come inside and see for yourself.

1124
01:07:44.208 --> 01:07:45.208
No.

1125
01:07:53.041 --> 01:07:58.000
Once again. we see the structures
inherent in our patriarchal society.

1126
01:07:58.583 --> 01:08:02.208
If I was a man. no one
would have been upset by my comment.

1127
01:08:02.291 --> 01:08:06.291
However. women aren't allowed
to speak like that. Ever.

1128
01:08:06.375 --> 01:08:08.083
Because we must be kind.

1129
01:08:08.166 --> 01:08:12.333
warm. nice. motherly. and empathetic.

1130
01:08:22.208 --> 01:08:24.125
Look. it's a Celtic tail.

1131
01:08:28.666 --> 01:08:30.291
We'll expose this guy.

1132
01:08:30.375 --> 01:08:31.666
Um… we can't be…

1133
01:08:31.750 --> 01:08:35.000
We have to refrain-refrain from…
We can't be physically violent.

1134
01:08:35.708 --> 01:08:38.166
Is that what you think of me?
I am not violent. I'm a policeman.

1135
01:08:38.250 --> 01:08:39.666
No!

1136
01:08:39.750 --> 01:08:40.750
Yes.

1137
01:08:41.833 --> 01:08:42.958
So you'll have to arrest him?

1138
01:08:43.041 --> 01:08:45.166
I wh… I'll make him come clean.

1139
01:08:45.750 --> 01:08:47.208
Ah. Okay.

1140
01:08:48.708 --> 01:08:50.916
And I'll give him a negative review.

1141
01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:54.083
"With disdainful regards…"

1142
01:08:54.583 --> 01:08:55.583
No.

1143
01:08:57.291 --> 01:08:59.750
"With much contempt."

1144
01:09:00.333 --> 01:09:01.333
No.

1145
01:09:02.083 --> 01:09:06.458
"With sincere contempt.
Ursula Brandmeier."

1146
01:09:07.041 --> 01:09:08.083
No turning back.

1147
01:09:39.625 --> 01:09:40.875
Come on…

1148
01:09:43.916 --> 01:09:45.166
<i>Babs?</i>

1149
01:09:46.916 --> 01:09:47.916
Babs?

1150
01:10:00.791 --> 01:10:01.625
You seen Babs?

1151
01:10:02.458 --> 01:10:03.625
No.

1152
01:10:04.666 --> 01:10:05.666
Too bad…

1153
01:10:06.791 --> 01:10:08.708
Wait. Uh…

1154
01:10:08.791 --> 01:10:11.125
- She just went up the mountain.
- Why would she do that?

1155
01:10:12.250 --> 01:10:13.833
Probably to find her man Nodon

1156
01:10:13.916 --> 01:10:16.750
and live happily
for the rest of their little hippie lives.

1157
01:10:16.833 --> 01:10:18.625
- Hm.
- Oh God.

1158
01:10:18.708 --> 01:10:21.416
A storm is coming.
We better go look for her.

1159
01:10:22.458 --> 01:10:25.083
We? I mean. isn't that dangerous?

1160
01:10:25.583 --> 01:10:26.583
Hm.

1161
01:10:28.125 --> 01:10:29.791
I'm all about safety.

1162
01:10:33.291 --> 01:10:36.250
You can stay here if you want.
I won't pressure any of you.

1163
01:10:38.000 --> 01:10:39.500
I'm coming.

1164
01:10:41.291 --> 01:10:44.875
Yeah. I can do something nice
for others now and then.

1165
01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:47.750
Don't worry. Torsten.

1166
01:10:47.833 --> 01:10:50.041
We will clear Nodon's name.

1167
01:10:51.083 --> 01:10:53.500
The others have no idea
what they are talking about.

1168
01:10:54.041 --> 01:10:55.833
Nodon was always good to us.

1169
01:12:32.958 --> 01:12:34.375
Oh God.

1170
01:12:38.041 --> 01:12:39.750
He lied. They were right.

1171
01:12:58.125 --> 01:13:01.125
Hey. it's okay.
You can go back if you want.

1172
01:13:01.208 --> 01:13:02.833
Roxy and I will keep going.

1173
01:13:24.791 --> 01:13:27.333
Torsten. calm down.

1174
01:13:27.416 --> 01:13:28.916
Torsten. stop it!

1175
01:13:30.791 --> 01:13:32.458
We don't need Nodon anymore.

1176
01:13:33.458 --> 01:13:35.250
We can make it on our own.

1177
01:14:00.583 --> 01:14:01.416
Babs!

1178
01:14:03.291 --> 01:14:04.750
- Ziggy!
- You're okay!

1179
01:14:04.833 --> 01:14:06.166
I'm so happy we found you!

1180
01:14:06.250 --> 01:14:09.583
We were so worried about you. Going up in
weather this bad is completely reckless!

1181
01:14:09.666 --> 01:14:10.833
I'm sorry.

1182
01:14:11.416 --> 01:14:14.333
And you guys were right.
Nodon is a total fraud.

1183
01:14:14.416 --> 01:14:15.916
His hut is completely abandoned.

1184
01:14:16.000 --> 01:14:17.708
You went up there?

1185
01:14:19.333 --> 01:14:21.958
Torsten. that's enough. Now sit.

1186
01:14:23.250 --> 01:14:24.250
Sit.

1187
01:14:33.291 --> 01:14:35.083
So let's go now.

1188
01:14:35.166 --> 01:14:38.458
Before we get struck by lightning
or the path is flooded or…

1189
01:14:39.416 --> 01:14:41.291
Urschi!

1190
01:14:44.250 --> 01:14:45.583
Urschi!

1191
01:14:45.666 --> 01:14:47.458
Urschi!

1192
01:14:47.541 --> 01:14:50.166
Urschi!

1193
01:14:50.250 --> 01:14:52.750
Urschi!

1194
01:14:52.833 --> 01:14:55.083
Oh no. no. no. Shit!

1195
01:14:55.166 --> 01:14:56.583
So what do we do now?

1196
01:14:57.416 --> 01:14:59.916
- We have to save her!
- I don't have phone service!

1197
01:15:02.583 --> 01:15:05.125
Hakan. I bet Roxy can find her.

1198
01:15:09.250 --> 01:15:11.416
Roxy. search! Search!

1199
01:15:11.916 --> 01:15:13.750
Go. go. go!

1200
01:15:18.250 --> 01:15:19.250
Wait. what?

1201
01:15:19.750 --> 01:15:23.583
They went up the mountain in a storm?
Why would they do that? Are they crazy?

1202
01:15:23.666 --> 01:15:25.708
Because your cover's been blown.

1203
01:15:25.791 --> 01:15:29.250
They snooped in your room
and found all of your Celtic crap.

1204
01:15:31.750 --> 01:15:34.708
They have no experience up there.
Come. Heidi.

1205
01:15:34.791 --> 01:15:36.250
What are you doing?

1206
01:15:36.916 --> 01:15:38.458
I'm going after them.

1207
01:15:38.541 --> 01:15:39.958
Don't you die too!

1208
01:15:41.875 --> 01:15:42.875
Roxy has a scent!

1209
01:15:44.375 --> 01:15:45.375
Urschi!

1210
01:15:47.458 --> 01:15:49.166
Urschi!

1211
01:15:49.250 --> 01:15:51.291
- Urschi!
- Urschi!

1212
01:15:51.375 --> 01:15:52.791
Urschi!

1213
01:15:52.875 --> 01:15:54.125
Urschi!

1214
01:15:56.750 --> 01:15:58.125
- You hear that?
- Yeah.

1215
01:15:58.208 --> 01:15:59.458
That's Brenda.

1216
01:15:59.541 --> 01:16:00.375
- Urschi!
- Urschi!

1217
01:16:07.083 --> 01:16:08.083
Urschi.

1218
01:16:10.750 --> 01:16:11.875
Oh my God.

1219
01:16:12.416 --> 01:16:13.416
Oh!

1220
01:16:14.541 --> 01:16:16.375
- Urschi.
- Oh no. Urschi.

1221
01:16:16.458 --> 01:16:17.791
Are you okay?

1222
01:16:18.666 --> 01:16:20.416
- Hey. you okay?
- Oh!

1223
01:16:22.458 --> 01:16:23.666
I think so.

1224
01:16:24.416 --> 01:16:26.416
- Ah!
- Hello!

1225
01:16:28.750 --> 01:16:31.791
You wonderful… sweet girl.

1226
01:16:31.875 --> 01:16:34.291
I'm sorry I dragged you into this mess.

1227
01:16:34.375 --> 01:16:36.875
- Urschi. you look a little--
- Different.

1228
01:16:39.375 --> 01:16:40.500
Uh…

1229
01:16:47.583 --> 01:16:49.958
I remember how I know you now!

1230
01:16:50.458 --> 01:16:54.250
This is Ursula Brandmeier.
the candidate for European parliament.

1231
01:16:55.458 --> 01:16:56.833
Oh my God. yeah!

1232
01:16:56.916 --> 01:16:59.375
She had that super awkward appearance
on that talk show.

1233
01:16:59.458 --> 01:17:01.333
She's the dog hater.

1234
01:17:01.416 --> 01:17:03.291
That's why she's so nasty to Brenda.

1235
01:17:03.375 --> 01:17:05.958
Well. she may not like dogs.
but at least she's doing all this

1236
01:17:06.041 --> 01:17:07.583
for her disabled friend.

1237
01:17:08.958 --> 01:17:11.583
I… I don't have a disabled friend.

1238
01:17:12.416 --> 01:17:14.208
Everything I told you was a lie.

1239
01:17:15.375 --> 01:17:17.000
And Brenda is only with me because

1240
01:17:17.083 --> 01:17:19.333
my advisor thought
it'd be good for my image

1241
01:17:19.416 --> 01:17:21.375
if I had a shelter dog.

1242
01:17:21.458 --> 01:17:23.708
What the heck is wrong with you?

1243
01:17:23.791 --> 01:17:25.666
Why lie to us all?

1244
01:17:26.458 --> 01:17:28.625
Babs. I'll explain it to you another time.

1245
01:17:29.541 --> 01:17:30.916
Can you stand up?

1246
01:17:33.500 --> 01:17:36.291
Ow! That hurts bad. it's my ankle.

1247
01:17:36.375 --> 01:17:37.750
I can't move.

1248
01:17:37.833 --> 01:17:39.750
Leave me here and send help.

1249
01:17:39.833 --> 01:17:43.791
and if you don't hate me too much.
please take Brenda back with you.

1250
01:17:44.541 --> 01:17:45.958
Nodon.

1251
01:17:48.208 --> 01:17:50.708
- Is she the only one who's hurt?
- Yeah.

1252
01:17:53.166 --> 01:17:55.083
When we get back.
we'll talk about everything.

1253
01:17:56.416 --> 01:17:57.416
Okay.

1254
01:18:00.541 --> 01:18:01.500
Ow!

1255
01:18:02.166 --> 01:18:04.125
It's not broken. That's good.

1256
01:18:06.291 --> 01:18:07.375
Ursula Brandmeier.

1257
01:18:08.083 --> 01:18:09.958
I'm not completely sure of that.
Simon Reisinger.

1258
01:18:12.708 --> 01:18:13.708
So how did you find her?

1259
01:18:26.958 --> 01:18:28.750
Stupid idiots. all of you.

1260
01:18:29.500 --> 01:18:31.750
If you really want to go off yourselves.

1261
